{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:08:42,356", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop Match Analyzer module to compare parsed resume data against job requirements and compute a resume-job match score with analysis.\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Build Question Generation Engine to produce technical and behavioral interview questions based on extracted job requirements.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Job Description Analysis module to parse job description text and extract required skills, responsibilities, and role context.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass JobDescriptionAnalyzer:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_text):\\n        self.job_description_text = job_description_text\\n        self.required_skills = []\\n        self.responsibilities = []\\n        self.role_context = \\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def extract_skills(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extracts required skills from the job description text using regex.\\n        This is a basic implementation and can be enhanced with NLP techniques.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Basic regex for skills (can be expanded)\\n        skill_patterns = [\\n            r\\\"(Python|Java|C++|JavaScript|SQL|AWS|Azure|GCP|Docker|Kubernetes|React|Angular|Vue\\\\.js)\\\",\\n            r\\\"(machine learning|deep learning|natural language processing)\\\",\\n            r\\\"(data analysis|data mining|statistical modeling)\\\",\\n            r\\\"(project management|agile methodologies|scrum)\\\",\\n            r\\\"(communication skills|leadership skills|problem-solving skills)\\\"\\n        ]\\n\\n        for pattern in skill_patterns:\\n            matches = re.findall(pattern, self.job_description_text, re.IGNORECASE)\\n            self.required_skills.extend(matches)\\n\\n        self.required_skills = list(set(self.required_skills)) # Remove duplicates\\n        return self.required_skills\\n\\n    def extract_responsibilities(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extracts responsibilities from the job description text.\\n        This is a basic implementation that looks for sentences containing keywords\\n        related to responsibilities.  Can be enhanced with NLP for better accuracy.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        responsibility_keywords = [\\\"responsible for\\\", \\\"duties include\\\", \\\"will be responsible\\\", \\\"accountable for\\\", \\\"key responsibilities\\\"]\\n        sentences = re.split(r'[.\\\\n]', self.job_description_text)  # Split into sentences\\n        for sentence in sentences:\\n            for keyword in responsibility_keywords:\\n                if keyword in sentence.lower():\\n                    self.responsibilities.append(sentence.strip())\\n                    break # avoid duplicates\\n\\n        return self.responsibilities\\n\\n    def extract_role_context(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extracts the role context from the job description text.\\n        This is a basic implementation that looks for introductory paragraphs.\\n        Can be improved with more sophisticated NLP techniques for context extraction.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Assuming the first few sentences describe the role context.\\n        sentences = re.split(r'[.\\\\n]', self.job_description_text)\\n        self.role_context = \\\". \\\".join(sentences[:3]).strip()  # Take first 3 sentences\\n\\n        return self.role_context\\n\\n    def analyze_job_description(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Performs the complete job description analysis.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.extract_skills()\\n        self.extract_responsibilities()\\n        self.extract_role_context()\\n\\n        return {\\n            \\\"required_skills\\\": self.required_skills,\\n            \\\"responsibilities\\\": self.responsibilities,\\n            \\\"role_context\\\": self.role_context\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    job_description = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    We are looking for a skilled Python Developer to join our team.  The ideal candidate will be responsible for developing and maintaining web applications.  Duties include writing clean, efficient code and collaborating with other developers.  Experience with React is a plus.  Key responsibilities are designing and implementing new features.  The candidate should also possess strong communication skills.\\n\\n    This is an exciting opportunity to work on cutting-edge technology.  We offer a competitive salary and benefits package.  Our company is a leader in the industry.\\n\\n    Required Skills: Python, React, SQL, Communication Skills\\n\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    analyzer = JobDescriptionAnalyzer(job_description)\\n    analysis_result = analyzer.analyze_job_description()\\n\\n    print(\\\"Required Skills:\\\", analysis_result[\\\"required_skills\\\"])\\n    print(\\\"Responsibilities:\\\", analysis_result[\\\"responsibilities\\\"])\\n    print(\\\"Role Context:\\\", analysis_result[\\\"role_context\\\"])\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:08:42.356740\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:08:43,476", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Develop Scoring Engine to aggregate match analysis and response evaluation into category scores across evaluation criteria.\\nTask task6:\\n  Objective: Implement Evaluation Report Generator to compile match analysis, interview summary, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendations into a .txt report.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Candidate Response Evaluation module to assess candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\ndef evaluate_candidate_response(question, answer, expected_keywords=None, relevant_topics=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates a candidate's response based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        question (str): The question asked to the candidate.\\n        answer (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_keywords (list, optional): A list of keywords that should ideally be present in the answer. Defaults to None.\\n        relevant_topics (list, optional): A list of relevant topics the answer should touch upon. Defaults to None.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing the evaluation scores and feedback.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    evaluation = {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being highly relevant)\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being very in-depth)\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being very confident)\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being completely accurate)\\n        \\\"feedback\\\": []  # List of feedback strings\\n    }\\n\\n    # Relevance Evaluation\\n    if not answer:\\n        evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = 0\\n        evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Candidate provided no answer.\\\")\\n    else:\\n        # Simple keyword-based relevance check\\n        if expected_keywords:\\n            keyword_count = sum(1 for keyword in expected_keywords if keyword.lower() in answer.lower())\\n            evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = min(10, (keyword_count / len(expected_keywords)) * 10 if len(expected_keywords) > 0 else 10)  # Avoid division by zero\\n            if keyword_count < len(expected_keywords):\\n                missing_keywords = [keyword for keyword in expected_keywords if keyword.lower() not in answer.lower()]\\n                evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(f\\\"Answer could have included more details about: {', '.join(missing_keywords)}.\\\")\\n\\n        if relevant_topics:\\n            topic_count = sum(1 for topic in relevant_topics if topic.lower() in answer.lower())\\n            evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = max(evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"],min(10, (topic_count / len(relevant_topics)) * 10 if len(relevant_topics) > 0 else 10))\\n        # Placeholder for more advanced NLP-based relevance scoring\\n\\n        evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = min(evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] + 2, 10) # Adding a small relevance score\\n\\n    # Depth Evaluation\\n    word_count = len(answer.split())\\n    if word_count < 50:\\n      evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] = min(5, word_count/10) #adjust scoring based on the word count\\n      evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Answer could have been more detailed.\\\")\\n\\n    elif word_count > 200:\\n        evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] = 8 # Reasonable score for in depth answer\\n    else:\\n        evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] = 6\\n\\n    # Confidence Evaluation (Subjective - needs to be assessed during the interview)\\n    # This is a placeholder - in a real application, this would be based on interviewer observation\\n    evaluation[\\\"confidence\\\"] = 7  # Example score - to be adjusted by the interviewer\\n    evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Confidence assessment based on interviewer observation.\\\")\\n\\n    # Technical Accuracy Evaluation (Needs domain-specific knowledge)\\n    # This is a placeholder - you'll need to implement the logic to assess technical accuracy based on the question and expected answer.\\n    evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] = 6 # Example score - to be adjusted by a technical expert.\\n    evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Technical accuracy assessment based on expert knowledge required.\\\")\\n\\n    return evaluation\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example usage\\n    question = \\\"Explain the concept of polymorphism in object-oriented programming.\\\"\\n    answer = \\\"Polymorphism allows objects of different classes to respond to the same method call in their own way.  It's important for code reusability.\\\"\\n    expected_keywords = [\\\"polymorphism\\\", \\\"object-oriented\\\", \\\"method\\\", \\\"class\\\", \\\"reusability\\\"]\\n    relevant_topics = [\\\"inheritance\\\", \\\"encapsulation\\\"]\\n    result = evaluate_candidate_response(question, answer, expected_keywords, relevant_topics)\\n    print(result)\\n\\n    question2 = \\\"What are some common software design patterns?\\\"\\n    answer2 = \\\"Singleton and Factory are good ones.\\\"\\n    expected_keywords2 = [\\\"design patterns\\\", \\\"singleton\\\", \\\"factory\\\"]\\n    relevant_topics2 = [\\\"creational\\\", \\\"structural\\\", \\\"behavioral\\\"]\\n    result2 = evaluate_candidate_response(question2,answer2,expected_keywords2, relevant_topics2)\\n    print(result2)\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:08:43.476484\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:08:44,094", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop Match Analyzer module to compare parsed resume data against job requirements and compute a resume-job match score with analysis.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Resume Parsing module to extract candidate skills, experience, education, and achievements from resume text.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass ResumeParser:\\n    def __init__(self, resume_text):\\n        self.resume_text = resume_text\\n        self.data = {}\\n\\n    def extract_skills(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts skills from the resume text.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        skills_keywords = [\\n            \\\"Python\\\", \\\"Java\\\", \\\"C++\\\", \\\"JavaScript\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"Angular\\\", \\\"Node.js\\\",\\n            \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"NoSQL\\\", \\\"MongoDB\\\", \\\"PostgreSQL\\\", \\\"AWS\\\", \\\"Azure\\\", \\\"GCP\\\",\\n            \\\"Docker\\\", \\\"Kubernetes\\\", \\\"Git\\\", \\\"Jenkins\\\", \\\"Terraform\\\", \\\"Ansible\\\",\\n            \\\"Machine Learning\\\", \\\"Deep Learning\\\", \\\"Data Analysis\\\", \\\"Project Management\\\",\\n            \\\"Communication\\\", \\\"Leadership\\\", \\\"Problem Solving\\\"\\n        ]\\n        extracted_skills = []\\n        for skill in skills_keywords:\\n            if re.search(r'\\\\b' + re.escape(skill) + r'\\\\b', self.resume_text, re.IGNORECASE):\\n                extracted_skills.append(skill)\\n        self.data['skills'] = extracted_skills\\n        return extracted_skills\\n\\n    def extract_experience(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts work experience from the resume text.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        experience_sections = re.split(r'\\\\bExperience\\\\b|\\\\bWork Experience\\\\b', self.resume_text, flags=re.IGNORECASE)[1:]\\n        experience_list = []\\n        for section in experience_sections:\\n            # Split each section into individual experience entries based on common separators\\n            entries = re.split(r'\\\\n(?=[A-Z][a-z]+\\\\s[A-Z][a-z]+|\\\\d{4}\\\\s*[-–—]\\\\s*\\\\d{4}|\\\\d{2}/\\\\d{4}\\\\s*[-–—]\\\\s*\\\\d{2}/\\\\d{4})', section)  # Updated regex\\n            for entry in entries:\\n                entry = entry.strip()\\n                if entry:\\n                    experience_list.append(entry)\\n        self.data['experience'] = experience_list\\n        return experience_list\\n\\n    def extract_education(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts education information from the resume text.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        education_sections = re.split(r'\\\\bEducation\\\\b', self.resume_text, flags=re.IGNORECASE)[1:]\\n        education_list = []\\n        for section in education_sections:\\n            entries = section.split('\\\\n')\\n            for entry in entries:\\n                entry = entry.strip()\\n                if entry:\\n                    education_list.append(entry)\\n        self.data['education'] = education_list\\n        return education_list\\n\\n    def extract_achievements(self):\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts achievements and awards from the resume text.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         achievement_keywords = [\\\"Achievement\\\", \\\"Achievements\\\", \\\"Award\\\", \\\"Awards\\\", \\\"Recognition\\\"]\\n         achievements = []\\n         for keyword in achievement_keywords:\\n            sections = re.split(r'\\\\b' + re.escape(keyword) + r's?\\\\b', self.resume_text, flags=re.IGNORECASE)[1:]\\n            for section in sections:\\n                entries = section.split('\\\\n')\\n                for entry in entries:\\n                    entry = entry.strip()\\n                    if entry:\\n                        achievements.append(entry)\\n         self.data['achievements'] = achievements\\n         return achievements\\n\\n    def parse(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Parses the resume text and extracts relevant information.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.extract_skills()\\n        self.extract_experience()\\n        self.extract_education()\\n        self.extract_achievements()\\n        return self.data\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage (replace with actual resume text)\\n    resume_text = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    John Doe\\n    john.doe@example.com\\n    (123) 456-7890\\n\\n    Summary\\n    Experienced software engineer with a passion for developing innovative solutions.\\n\\n    Skills\\n    Python, Java, JavaScript, SQL, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, Git, Machine Learning\\n\\n    Experience\\n    Software Engineer, ABC Company, 2018-2023\\n    - Developed and maintained web applications using Python and JavaScript.\\n    - Deployed applications to AWS using Docker and Kubernetes.\\n\\n    Software Developer, XYZ Company, 2016-2018\\n    - Designed and implemented REST APIs using Java and Spring Boot.\\n    - Managed databases using SQL and PostgreSQL.\\n\\n    Education\\n    Bachelor of Science in Computer Science, University of California, 2016\\n\\n    Achievements\\n    - Employee of the Month, ABC Company, 2020\\n    - Published research paper on Machine Learning, 2015\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    parser = ResumeParser(resume_text)\\n    parsed_data = parser.parse()\\n\\n    print(parsed_data)\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:08:44.094730\"\n}"}
