{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:08:58,223", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:08:58.223354\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement Resume Parsing module to extract candidate skills, experience, education, and achievements from resume text.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass ResumeParser:\\n    def __init__(self, resume_text):\\n        self.resume_text = resume_text\\n        self.data = {}\\n\\n    def extract_skills(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts skills from the resume text.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        skills_keywords = [\\n            \\\"Python\\\", \\\"Java\\\", \\\"C++\\\", \\\"JavaScript\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"Angular\\\", \\\"Node.js\\\",\\n            \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"NoSQL\\\", \\\"MongoDB\\\", \\\"PostgreSQL\\\", \\\"AWS\\\", \\\"Azure\\\", \\\"GCP\\\",\\n            \\\"Docker\\\", \\\"Kubernetes\\\", \\\"Git\\\", \\\"Jenkins\\\", \\\"Terraform\\\", \\\"Ansible\\\",\\n            \\\"...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The extracted data is currently unstructured (just lists of strings). For downstream tasks, it’s better to parse entries into dictionaries with fields (e.g., title, company, dates for experience; degree, institution, year for education).\\n2. The achievements extraction loops over all keywords separately, causing duplicate entries. We should isolate the “Achievements” section once and then split it.\\n3. Experience and education regexes can be tightened to capture components.\\n4. Gracefully handle missing sections by returning empty lists.\\n5. Improve comments and method order for readability.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Optional\\n\\nclass ResumeParser:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Parses resume text to extract structured information:\\n      - skills: List[str]\\n      - experience: List[Dict[str, Optional[str]]]\\n      - education: List[Dict[str, Optional[str]]]\\n      - achievements: List[str]\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    SECTION_HEADERS = {\\n        'skills': r'\\\\bSkills\\\\b',\\n        'experience': r'\\\\bExperience\\\\b|\\\\bWork Experience\\\\b',\\n        'education': r'\\\\bEducation\\\\b',\\n        'achievements': r'\\\\bAchievements?\\\\b|\\\\bAwards?\\\\b'\\n    }\\n\\n    def __init__(self, text: str):\\n        self.text = text\\n        self.data = {\\n            'skills': [],\\n            'experience': [],\\n            'education': [],\\n            'achievements': []\\n        }\\n\\n    def _extract_section(self, name: str) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the text under a given section header up to the next header or end.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pattern = (\\n            rf\\\"(?P<header>{self.SECTION_HEADERS[name]})\\\"\\n            r\\\"(?P<content>.*?)(?=\\\\n[A-Z][a-z]+:|\\\\Z)\\\"\\n        )\\n        match = re.search(pattern, self.text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\\n        return match.group('content').strip() if match else ''\\n\\n    def extract_skills(self) -> List[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extract skills by splitting on commas or line breaks in the Skills section.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        content = self._extract_section('skills')\\n        if not content:\\n            return []\\n        # Split by commas or newlines\\n        raw = re.split(r'[,\\\\n]+', content)\\n        skills = [s.strip() for s in raw if s.strip()]\\n        self.data['skills'] = skills\\n        return skills\\n\\n    def extract_experience(self) -> List[Dict[str, Optional[str]]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extract each experience entry as a dict with:\\n          - title\\n          - company\\n          - start_date\\n          - end_date\\n          - details (joined bullet lines)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        content = self._extract_section('experience')\\n        if not content:\\n            return []\\n        entries = re.split(r'\\\\n(?=[A-Za-z].+,\\\\s*[A-Za-z].+,\\\\s*\\\\d{4})', content.strip())\\n        exp_list = []\\n        for entry in entries:\\n            lines = [l.strip() for l in entry.split('\\\\n') if l.strip()]\\n            header = lines[0]\\n            # e.g., \\\"Software Engineer, ABC Company, 2018-2023\\\"\\n            hdr_match = re.match(\\n                r'(?P<title>[^,]+),\\\\s*(?P<company>[^,]+),\\\\s*'\\n                r'(?P<start>\\\\d{4})(?:\\\\s*[-–—]\\\\s*(?P<end>\\\\d{4}|Present))?', header\\n            )\\n            details = lines[1:]  # bullets or descriptions\\n            exp_list.append({\\n                'title': hdr_match.group('title').strip() if hdr_match else None,\\n                'company': hdr_match.group('company').strip() if hdr_match else None,\\n                'start_date': hdr_match.group('start') if hdr_match else None,\\n                'end_date': hdr_match.group('end') if hdr_match else None,\\n                'details': details\\n            })\\n        self.data['experience'] = exp_list\\n        return exp_list\\n\\n    def extract_education(self) -> List[Dict[str, Optional[str]]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extract each education entry as a dict with:\\n          - degree\\n          - institution\\n          - year\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        content = self._extract_section('education')\\n        if not content:\\n            return []\\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in content.split('\\\\n') if l.strip()]\\n        edu_list = []\\n        for line in lines:\\n            # e.g., \\\"Bachelor of Science in Computer Science, University X, 2016\\\"\\n            m = re.match(\\n                r'(?P<degree>.+?),\\\\s*(?P<institution>.+?),\\\\s*(?P<year>\\\\d{4})', line\\n            )\\n            edu_list.append({\\n                'degree': m.group('degree').strip() if m else None,\\n                'institution': m.group('institution').strip() if m else None,\\n                'year': m.group('year') if m else None\\n            })\\n        self.data['education'] = edu_list\\n        return edu_list\\n\\n    def extract_achievements(self) -> List[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extract bullet-point achievements from the Achievements/Awards section.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        content = self._extract_section('achievements')\\n        if not content:\\n            return []\\n        # Remove the header line if it appears in content\\n        lines = [l.strip('-•* ').strip() for l in content.split('\\\\n') if l.strip()]\\n        self.data['achievements'] = lines\\n        return lines\\n\\n    def parse(self) -> Dict[str, List]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Run all extractors and return structured data.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.extract_skills()\\n        self.extract_experience()\\n        self.extract_education()\\n        self.extract_achievements()\\n        return self.data\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example usage\\n    resume_text = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    John Doe\\n    john.doe@example.com\\n    (123) 456-7890\\n\\n    Skills\\n    Python, Java, JavaScript\\n    AWS\\n    Docker\\n\\n    Experience\\n    Software Engineer, ABC Company, 2018-2023\\n    - Developed web apps in Python.\\n    - Deployed with Docker.\\n\\n    Software Developer, XYZ Company, 2016-2018\\n    - Built REST APIs.\\n\\n    Education\\n    Bachelor of Science in Computer Science, University of California, 2016\\n\\n    Achievements\\n    • Employee of the Month, ABC Company, 2020\\n    • Published ML research, 2015\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    parser = ResumeParser(resume_text)\\n    parsed = parser.parse()\\n    print(parsed)\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:09:03,758", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Implement Candidate \",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 2,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```python\\ndef evaluate_candidate_response(question, answer, expected_keywords=None, relevant_topics=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates a candidate's response based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        question (str): The question asked to the candidate.\\n        answer (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_keywords (list, optional): A list of keywords that should ideally be present in the answer. Defaults to None.\\n        relevant_topics (list, optional): A list of relevant topics the answer should touch upon. Defaults to None.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing the evaluation scores and feedback.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    evaluation = {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being highly relevant)\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being very in-depth)\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being very confident)\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 0,  # Score from 0 to 10 (10 being completely accurate)\\n        \\\"feedback\\\": []  # List of feedback strings\\n    }\\n\\n    # Relevance Evaluation\\n    if not answer:\\n        evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = 0\\n        evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Candidate provided no answer.\\\")\\n    else:\\n        # Simple keyword-based relevance check\\n        if expected_keywords:\\n            keyword_count = sum(1 for keyword in expected_keywords if keyword.lower() in answer.lower())\\n            evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = min(10, (keyword_count / len(expected_keywords)) * 10 if len(expected_keywords) > 0 else 10)  # Avoid division by zero\\n            if keyword_count < len(expected_keywords):\\n                missing_keywords = [keyword for keyword in expected_keywords if keyword.lower() not in answer.lower()]\\n                evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(f\\\"Answer could have included more details about: {', '.join(missing_keywords)}.\\\")\\n\\n        if relevant_topics:\\n            topic_count = sum(1 for topic in relevant_topics if topic.lower() in answer.lower())\\n            evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = max(evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"],min(10, (topic_count / len(relevant_topics)) * 10 if len(relevant_topics) > 0 else 10))\\n        # Placeholder for more advanced NLP-based relevance scoring\\n\\n        evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] = min(evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] + 2, 10) # Adding a small relevance score\\n\\n    # Depth Evaluation\\n    word_count = len(answer.split())\\n    if word_count < 50:\\n      evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] = min(5, word_count/10) #adjust scoring based on the word count\\n      evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Answer could have been more detailed.\\\")\\n\\n    elif word_count > 200:\\n        evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] = 8 # Reasonable score for in depth answer\\n    else:\\n        evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] = 6\\n\\n    # Confidence Evaluation (Subjective - needs to be assessed during the interview)\\n    # This is a placeholder - in a real application, this would be based on interviewer observation\\n    evaluation[\\\"confidence\\\"] = 7  # Example score - to be adjusted by the interviewer\\n    evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Confidence assessment based on interviewer observation.\\\")\\n\\n    # Technical Accuracy Evaluation (Needs domain-specific knowledge)\\n    # This is a placeholder - you'll need to implement the logic to assess technical accuracy based on the question and expected answer.\\n    evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] = 6 # Example score - to be adjusted by a technical expert.\\n    evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"].append(\\\"Technical accuracy assessment based on expert knowledge required.\\\")\\n\\n    return evaluation\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example usage\\n    question = \\\"Explain the concept of polymorphism in object-oriented programming.\\\"\\n    answer = \\\"Polymorphism allows objects of different classes to respond to the same method call in their own way.  It's important for code reusability.\\\"\\n    expected_keywords = [\\\"polymorphism\\\", \\\"object-oriented\\\", \\\"method\\\", \\\"class\\\", \\\"reusability\\\"]\\n    relevant_topics = [\\\"inheritance\\\", \\\"encapsulation\\\"]\\n    result = evaluate_candidate_response(question, answer, expected_keywords, relevant_topics)\\n    print(result)\\n\\n    question2 = \\\"What are some common software design patterns?\\\"\\n    answer2 = \\\"Singleton and Factory are good ones.\\\"\\n    expected_keywords2 = [\\\"design patterns\\\", \\\"singleton\\\", \\\"factory\\\"]\\n    relevant_topics2 = [\\\"creational\\\", \\\"structural\\\", \\\"behavioral\\\"]\\n    result2 = evaluate_candidate_response(question2,answer2,expected_keywords2, relevant_topics2)\\n    print(result2)\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current implementation uses fixed placeholder scores for confidence and technical accuracy, without allowing dynamic assessment or overrides.\\n2. Depth scoring uses inconsistent thresholds and may return non-integer values on a 0–10 scale.\\n3. Relevance scoring separately handles keywords and topics but then arbitrarily adds 2 points, which can distort the scale.\\n4. Feedback messages can be more structured and informative.\\n5. The function signature should allow an interviewer or expert to supply observed confidence and technical accuracy if desired.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\ndef evaluate_candidate_response(\\n    question,\\n    answer,\\n    expected_keywords=None,\\n    relevant_topics=None,\\n    interviewer_confidence=None,\\n    expert_accuracy=None\\n):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates a candidate's response based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        question (str): The question asked to the candidate.\\n        answer (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_keywords (list of str, optional): Keywords that should appear in the answer.\\n        relevant_topics (list of str, optional): Topics the answer should address.\\n        interviewer_confidence (int, optional): Observer score (0–10) for candidate confidence.\\n        expert_accuracy (int, optional): Expert's score (0–10) for technical accuracy.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": int,\\n            \\\"depth\\\": int,\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": int,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": int,\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": list of str\\n        }\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    feedback = []\\n\\n    # Normalize inputs\\n    answer_lower = (answer or \\\"\\\").lower()\\n    word_count = len(answer_lower.split())\\n\\n    # 1. Relevance (0–10)\\n    relevance_score = 0\\n    total_checks = 0\\n    matches = 0\\n\\n    if expected_keywords:\\n        total_checks += len(expected_keywords)\\n        matches += sum(1 for kw in expected_keywords if kw.lower() in answer_lower)\\n    if relevant_topics:\\n        total_checks += len(relevant_topics)\\n        matches += sum(1 for topic in relevant_topics if topic.lower() in answer_lower)\\n\\n    if total_checks > 0:\\n        relevance_score = int(round((matches / total_checks) * 10))\\n        if matches < total_checks:\\n            missing = []\\n            for kw in (expected_keywords or []):\\n                if kw.lower() not in answer_lower:\\n                    missing.append(kw)\\n            for tp in (relevant_topics or []):\\n                if tp.lower() not in answer_lower:\\n                    missing.append(tp)\\n            feedback.append(\\\"Missing key points: \\\" + \\\", \\\".join(missing))\\n    else:\\n        # Fallback: short heuristic\\n        relevance_score = 5 if word_count > 0 else 0\\n        if word_count == 0:\\n            feedback.append(\\\"No answer provided.\\\")\\n\\n    # 2. Depth (0–10): scale word count\\n    #    <20 words -> 2, 20–50 -> 5, 50–100 -> 7, >100 -> 10\\n    if word_count == 0:\\n        depth_score = 0\\n    elif word_count < 20:\\n        depth_score = 2\\n        feedback.append(\\\"Answer is too brief; consider elaborating.\\\")\\n    elif word_count < 50:\\n        depth_score = 5\\n    elif word_count < 100:\\n        depth_score = 7\\n    else:\\n        depth_score = 10\\n\\n    # 3. Confidence (0–10)\\n    if interviewer_confidence is not None:\\n        confidence_score = max(0, min(10, interviewer_confidence))\\n    else:\\n        confidence_score = 5  # Neutral default\\n        feedback.append(\\\"No interviewer confidence score provided; using default.\\\")\\n\\n    # 4. Technical Accuracy (0–10)\\n    if expert_accuracy is not None:\\n        technical_accuracy_score = max(0, min(10, expert_accuracy))\\n    else:\\n        # Derive from expected_keywords overlap\\n        if expected_keywords:\\n            technical_accuracy_score = int(round((matches / len(expected_keywords)) * 10))\\n        else:\\n            technical_accuracy_score = 5  # Neutral default\\n        feedback.append(\\\"Technical accuracy auto-scored; consider expert review.\\\")\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": relevance_score,\\n        \\\"depth\\\": depth_score,\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": confidence_score,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": technical_accuracy_score,\\n        \\\"feedback\\\": feedback\\n    }\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    q1 = \\\"Explain polymorphism in OOP.\\\"\\n    a1 = \\\"Polymorphism lets different classes define the same interface method in their own way, improving code reuse.\\\"\\n    result1 = evaluate_candidate_response(\\n        q1,\\n        a1,\\n        expected_keywords=[\\\"polymorphism\\\", \\\"object-oriented\\\", \\\"interface\\\", \\\"reuse\\\"],\\n        relevant_topics=[\\\"inheritance\\\", \\\"dynamic binding\\\"],\\n        interviewer_confidence=8\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Evaluation 1:\\\", result1)\\n\\n    q2 = \\\"Name common software design patterns.\\\"\\n    a2 = \\\"Factory, Singleton, Observer.\\\"\\n    result2 = evaluate_candidate_response(\\n        q2,\\n        a2,\\n        expected_keywords=[\\\"design pattern\\\", \\\"factory\\\", \\\"singleton\\\", \\\"observer\\\"],\\n        relevant_topics=[\\\"creational\\\", \\\"behavioral\\\"],\\n        expert_accuracy=7\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Evaluation 2:\\\", result2)\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Develop Scoring Engine to aggregate match analysis and response evaluation into category scores across evaluation criteria.\\nTask task6:\\n  Objective: Implement Evaluation Report Generator to compile match analysis, interview summary, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendations into a .txt report.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Candidate Response Evaluation module to assess candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\ndef evaluate_candidate_response(\\n    question,\\n    answer,\\n    expected_keywords=None,\\n    relevant_topics=None,\\n    interviewer_confidence=None,\\n    expert_accuracy=None\\n):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates a candidate's response based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        question (str): The question asked to the candidate.\\n        answer (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_keywords (list of str, optional): Keywords that should appear in the answer.\\n        relevant_topics (list of str, optional): Topics the answer should address.\\n        interviewer_confidence (int, optional): Observer score (0–10) for candidate confidence.\\n        expert_accuracy (int, optional): Expert's score (0–10) for technical accuracy.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": int,\\n            \\\"depth\\\": int,\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": int,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": int,\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": list of str\\n        }\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    feedback = []\\n\\n    # Normalize inputs\\n    answer_lower = (answer or \\\"\\\").lower()\\n    word_count = len(answer_lower.split())\\n\\n    # 1. Relevance (0–10)\\n    relevance_score = 0\\n    total_checks = 0\\n    matches = 0\\n\\n    if expected_keywords:\\n        total_checks += len(expected_keywords)\\n        matches += sum(1 for kw in expected_keywords if kw.lower() in answer_lower)\\n    if relevant_topics:\\n        total_checks += len(relevant_topics)\\n        matches += sum(1 for topic in relevant_topics if topic.lower() in answer_lower)\\n\\n    if total_checks > 0:\\n        relevance_score = int(round((matches / total_checks) * 10))\\n        if matches < total_checks:\\n            missing = []\\n            for kw in (expected_keywords or []):\\n                if kw.lower() not in answer_lower:\\n                    missing.append(kw)\\n            for tp in (relevant_topics or []):\\n                if tp.lower() not in answer_lower:\\n                    missing.append(tp)\\n            feedback.append(\\\"Missing key points: \\\" + \\\", \\\".join(missing))\\n    else:\\n        # Fallback: short heuristic\\n        relevance_score = 5 if word_count > 0 else 0\\n        if word_count == 0:\\n            feedback.append(\\\"No answer provided.\\\")\\n\\n    # 2. Depth (0–10): scale word count\\n    #    <20 words -> 2, 20–50 -> 5, 50–100 -> 7, >100 -> 10\\n    if word_count == 0:\\n        depth_score = 0\\n    elif word_count < 20:\\n        depth_score = 2\\n        feedback.append(\\\"Answer is too brief; consider elaborating.\\\")\\n    elif word_count < 50:\\n        depth_score = 5\\n    elif word_count < 100:\\n        depth_score = 7\\n    else:\\n        depth_score = 10\\n\\n    # 3. Confidence (0–10)\\n    if interviewer_confidence is not None:\\n        confidence_score = max(0, min(10, interviewer_confidence))\\n    else:\\n        confidence_score = 5  # Neutral default\\n        feedback.append(\\\"No interviewer confidence score provided; using default.\\\")\\n\\n    # 4. Technical Accuracy (0–10)\\n    if expert_accuracy is not None:\\n        technical_accuracy_score = max(0, min(10, expert_accuracy))\\n    else:\\n        # Derive from expected_keywords overlap\\n        if expected_keywords:\\n            technical_accuracy_score = int(round((matches / len(expected_keywords)) * 10))\\n        else:\\n            technical_accuracy_score = 5  # Neutral default\\n        feedback.append(\\\"Technical accuracy auto-scored; consider expert review.\\\")\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": relevance_score,\\n        \\\"depth\\\": depth_score,\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": confidence_score,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": technical_accuracy_score,\\n        \\\"feedback\\\": feedback\\n    }\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:09:03.758737\"\n}"}
