{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:09:12,770", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:09:12.770146\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Build Question Generation Engine to produce technical and behavioral interview questions based on extracted job requirements.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass QuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, required_skills, responsibilities, role_context):\\n        self.required_skills = required_skills\\n        self.responsibilities = responsibilities\\n        self.role_context = role_context\\n\\n    def generate_technical_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical interview questions based on the required skills.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        technical_questions = []\\n        if \\\"Python\\\" in self.required_skills...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The behavioral questions are static and do not utilize the `responsibilities` or `role_context` fields to tailor questions.  \\n2. The technical questions do not cover some listed skills (e.g., React, Communication Skills) or provide a generic fallback for unrecognized skills.  \\n3. The code can be simplified and made more extensible by using a skill‐to‐template mapping instead of hardcoded blocks.  \\n4. The follow‐up generator can at least reference the role context to produce more targeted prompts.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass QuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, required_skills, responsibilities, role_context):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        required_skills: list of skill strings (e.g., [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"React\\\"])\\n        responsibilities: list of responsibility strings\\n        role_context: a string describing the role and team context\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.required_skills = [s.lower() for s in required_skills]\\n        self.responsibilities = responsibilities\\n        self.role_context = role_context\\n\\n        # Predefined templates for known skills\\n        self.tech_templates = {\\n            \\\"python\\\": [\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe how decorators work in Python and provide an example use case.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the Global Interpreter Lock (GIL) in Python? How does it affect concurrency?\\\",\\n                \\\"How does Python manage memory under the hood?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain inheritance and polymorphism in Python with examples.\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"java\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is the difference between == and .equals() in Java?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the SOLID principles in Java OOP.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does garbage collection work in the JVM?\\\",\\n                \\\"When would you use an interface vs. an abstract class in Java?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe checked vs. unchecked exceptions in Java.\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"javascript\\\": [\\n                \\\"What are the differences between let, const, and var?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain closures in JavaScript and a scenario where you'd use them.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does prototypal inheritance operate in JS?\\\",\\n                \\\"What is event loop in JavaScript? How does it affect async code?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe when you'd choose arrow functions over regular functions.\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"react\\\": [\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between class components and functional components in React.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are React hooks? Give examples of useState and useEffect.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does React's virtual DOM work?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe how you would optimize a large React application for performance.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage global state in React? (Context, Redux, etc.)\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"sql\\\": [\\n                \\\"Explain INNER JOIN vs. LEFT JOIN with examples.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are database indexes and how do they improve performance?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe ACID properties in a relational database.\\\",\\n                \\\"How would you optimize a slow SQL query?\\\",\\n                \\\"When would you use a stored procedure?\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"aws\\\": [\\n                \\\"Compare EC2 and AWS Lambda. When would you use each?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are IAM roles and policies? How do you secure AWS resources?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain S3 storage classes and use cases.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe VPC, subnets, and route tables in AWS.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you monitor application performance on AWS?\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"docker\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of Docker, and how do containers differ from VMs?\\\",\\n                \\\"Write a simple Dockerfile for a Python web app.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage persistent data with Docker volumes?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain Docker Compose and when you'd use it.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you optimize Docker images for smaller size?\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"kubernetes\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is a Kubernetes Pod, and how does it differ from a container?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain Deployments and Services in Kubernetes.\\\",\\n                \\\"How would you roll out a zero-downtime update in K8s?\\\",\\n                \\\"What is a StatefulSet, and when is it used?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you handle secrets in Kubernetes?\\\"\\n            ]\\n        }\\n\\n    def generate_technical_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a list of technical questions based on required_skills.\\n        Unknown skills get a generic question template.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        all_questions = []\\n        for skill in self.required_skills:\\n            if skill in self.tech_templates:\\n                all_questions.extend(self.tech_templates[skill])\\n            else:\\n                # Generic fallback\\n                all_questions.append(\\n                    f\\\"Explain your experience with {skill} and describe a challenging problem you solved using it.\\\"\\n                )\\n        random.shuffle(all_questions)\\n        return all_questions[:min(num_questions, len(all_questions))]\\n\\n    def generate_behavioral_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates behavioral questions by combining:\\n          - Generic behavioral templates\\n          - Role-specific questions derived from responsibilities and role_context\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        generic = [\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you had to work under pressure to meet a deadline.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to deal with a difficult team member. How did you handle it?\\\",\\n            \\\"Give an example of making a decision with incomplete information.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you failed. What did you learn?\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a time you had to adapt to significant change.\\\",\\n        ]\\n\\n        # Tailored questions from responsibilities\\n        tailored = []\\n        for resp in self.responsibilities:\\n            tailored.append(\\n                f\\\"Give an example of when you {resp.lower()}. What was your approach and outcome?\\\"\\n            )\\n\\n        # Incorporate role context\\n        context_question = f\\\"Considering our context ('{self.role_context}'), how would you ensure success in this role?\\\"\\n\\n        combined = generic + tailored + [context_question]\\n        random.shuffle(combined)\\n        return combined[:min(num_questions, len(combined))]\\n\\n    def generate_follow_up_questions(self, answer, num_questions=2):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates follow-up questions by probing deeper into the answer\\n        and referencing role context for relevance.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        probes = [\\n            \\\"Can you elaborate on the steps you took?\\\",\\n            \\\"What specific challenges did you face and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            \\\"What was the impact of your actions on the project or team?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you measure success in that situation?\\\",\\n            \\\"If you could revisit that, what would you do differently?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you collaborate with stakeholders or teammates?\\\"\\n        ]\\n\\n        random.shuffle(probes)\\n        # Include a reference to role context if meaningful\\n        context_probe = f\\\"How would that experience translate to our context: '{self.role_context}'?\\\"\\n        probes.insert(0, context_probe)\\n\\n        return probes[:num_questions]\\n\\n    def generate_all_questions(self,\\n                               num_technical=5,\\n                               num_behavioral=5,\\n                               num_follow_up=2,\\n                               sample_answer=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns a dict with technical, behavioral, and optional follow-ups\\n        (if sample_answer is provided).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        result = {\\n            \\\"technical_questions\\\": self.generate_technical_questions(num_technical),\\n            \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": self.generate_behavioral_questions(num_behavioral)\\n        }\\n        if sample_answer:\\n            result[\\\"follow_up_questions\\\"] = self.generate_follow_up_questions(\\n                sample_answer, num_follow_up\\n            )\\n        return result\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Example usage\\n    required_skills = [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Communication Skills\\\"]\\n    responsibilities = [\\n        \\\"Develop and maintain web applications\\\",\\n        \\\"Write clean, efficient code\\\",\\n        \\\"Collaborate with other developers and stakeholders\\\"\\n    ]\\n    role_context = \\\"We are building a high-availability Python/React platform for real-time analytics.\\\"\\n\\n    qg = QuestionGenerator(required_skills, responsibilities, role_context)\\n    questions = qg.generate_all_questions(\\n        num_technical=3,\\n        num_behavioral=3,\\n        num_follow_up=2,\\n        sample_answer=\\\"I led the migration of our monolith to microservices under a tight deadline...\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n    print(\\\"Technical Questions:\\\")\\n    for q in questions[\\\"technical_questions\\\"]:\\n        print(\\\"-\\\", q)\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Questions:\\\")\\n    for q in questions[\\\"behavioral_questions\\\"]:\\n        print(\\\"-\\\", q)\\n\\n    if \\\"follow_up_questions\\\" in questions:\\n        print(\\\"\\\\nFollow-Up Questions:\\\")\\n        for q in questions[\\\"follow_up_questions\\\"]:\\n            print(\\\"-\\\", q)\\n```\"}"}
