{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:10:25,409", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:10:25.409911\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement Follow-up Question Generation module to generate additional interview questions based on candidate responses and previous evaluation.\", \"result\": \"```python\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_question, evaluation_summary=None, relevant_topics=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on the candidate's response,\\n    the previous question, and an optional evaluation summary.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's answer to the previous question.\\n        previous_question (str): The question the candidate was responding to.\\n        evaluation_summary (dict, optional): Su...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The clarification question uses a raw slice of the response which may cut phrases awkwardly.\\n2. The logic for depth and challenge follow-ups is too simplistic and doesn’t reference specific concepts or steps.\\n3. There’s no specific “example” or “trade-off” follow-up to surface practical experience or design decisions.\\n4. The code would benefit from extracting a key concept from the candidate’s response to personalize questions.\\n5. The helper for key-phrase extraction is missing, so the “clarification” question may not work as intended.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\nfrom collections import Counter\\n\\ndef _extract_key_phrases(text, max_phrases=1):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Naively extract candidate’s most frequent multi-word phrases.\\n    For production use, replace with NLP-based extraction.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Find all words longer than 4 characters\\n    words = re.findall(r'\\\\b\\\\w{5,}\\\\b', text.lower())\\n    if not words:\\n        return []\\n    # Return the most common word(s) as a proxy for key concept\\n    common = [w for w, _ in Counter(words).most_common(max_phrases)]\\n    return common\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response,\\n                                 previous_question,\\n                                 evaluation_summary=None,\\n                                 relevant_topics=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates targeted follow-up interview questions.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): Candidate’s latest answer.\\n        previous_question (str): The question they were answering.\\n        evaluation_summary (dict, optional): {\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": [str],        # e.g., [\\\"too brief\\\", \\\"lack of examples\\\"]\\n            \\\"weaknesses\\\": [str]       # e.g., [\\\"unit testing\\\", \\\"scalability\\\"]\\n        }\\n        relevant_topics (list of str, optional): Topics to tie back to.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list of str: Tailored follow-up questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    follow_ups = []\\n\\n    # 1. Clarification: extract a key phrase or fallback to the previous question\\n    key_phrases = _extract_key_phrases(candidate_response, max_phrases=1)\\n    if key_phrases:\\n        follow_ups.append(f\\\"Can you elaborate on what you meant by '{key_phrases[0]}'?\\\")\\n    else:\\n        follow_ups.append(f\\\"Could you clarify your approach when answering: '{previous_question}'?\\\")\\n\\n    # 2. Depth: ask for step-by-step details\\n    follow_ups.append(\\\"Could you walk me through the steps you took in more detail?\\\")\\n\\n    # 3. Real-world Example\\n    follow_ups.append(\\\"Can you share a specific example or project where you applied this approach?\\\")\\n\\n    # 4. Trade-offs / Alternatives\\n    follow_ups.append(\\n        \\\"What other solutions did you consider, and why did you choose this one over alternatives?\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n    # 5. Potential Limitations\\n    follow_ups.append(\\n        f\\\"What potential pitfalls or limitations did you anticipate in your solution to '{previous_question}'?\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n    # 6. Addressing Feedback: if answer was too brief or lacked examples\\n    if evaluation_summary:\\n        for item in evaluation_summary.get(\\\"feedback\\\", []):\\n            if \\\"brief\\\" in item.lower():\\n                follow_ups.append(\\\"You mentioned this briefly—could you expand on that?\\\")\\n            if \\\"example\\\" in item.lower() or \\\"illustrate\\\" in item.lower():\\n                follow_ups.append(\\\"Can you illustrate your point with a concrete example?\\\")\\n\\n    # 7. Weakness-Targeted Follow-ups\\n    if evaluation_summary:\\n        for weakness in evaluation_summary.get(\\\"weaknesses\\\", []):\\n            follow_ups.append(\\n                f\\\"You noted '{weakness}' as an improvement area. How have you been working to strengthen that skill?\\\"\\n            )\\n\\n    # 8. Tie-back to Relevant Topics\\n    if relevant_topics:\\n        for topic in relevant_topics:\\n            follow_ups.append(f\\\"How does your experience relate to '{topic}' in practice?\\\")\\n\\n    return follow_ups\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:10:54,451", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Build Question Generation Engine to produce technical and behavioral interview questions based on extracted job requirements.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass QuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, required_skills, responsibilities, role_context):\\n        self.required_skills = required_skills\\n        self.responsibilities = responsibilities\\n        self.role_context = role_context\\n\\n    def generate_technical_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical interview questions based on the required skills.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        technical_questions = []\\n        if \\\"Python\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of decorators in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the Global Interpreter Lock (GIL) in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"How does memory management work in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the concept of inheritance and polymorphism in Python.\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"Java\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between == and .equals() in Java.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the principles of object-oriented programming in Java?\\\",\\n                \\\"How does garbage collection work in Java?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of interfaces and abstract classes in Java.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the different types of exceptions in Java?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"JavaScript\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between let, const, and var in JavaScript.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of the 'this' keyword in JavaScript?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the concept of closures in JavaScript.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does prototypal inheritance work in JavaScript?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the advantages of using arrow functions in JavaScript?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"SQL\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of using indexes in a database?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of stored procedures in SQL.\\\",\\n                \\\"How can you optimize a slow-running SQL query?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are ACID properties in the context of databases?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"AWS\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between EC2 and Lambda in AWS.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does S3 work and what are its use cases?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the purpose of IAM in AWS.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the difference between VPC and subnet in AWS?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you monitor and manage application performance in AWS?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"Docker\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"What is Docker and why is it used?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between Docker images and containers.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you create a Dockerfile?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage Docker volumes?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the advantages of using Docker Compose?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"Kubernetes\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"What is Kubernetes and why is it used?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between Pods, Deployments, and Services in Kubernetes.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage Kubernetes deployments?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you scale applications in Kubernetes?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are Kubernetes namespaces?\\\"\\n            ])\\n\\n        random.shuffle(technical_questions)\\n        return random.sample(technical_questions, min(num_questions, len(technical_questions)))\\n\\n    def generate_behavioral_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates behavioral interview questions based on the responsibilities and role context.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        behavioral_questions = [\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you had to work under pressure to meet a deadline.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to deal with a difficult team member. How did you handle it?\\\",\\n            \\\"Give me an example of a time you had to make a decision with incomplete information.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you failed. What did you learn from it?\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to adapt to a significant change in your work environment.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you had to convince a team to do something in a new way.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a time when you anticipated potential problems and took measures to prevent them.\\\",\\n            \\\"Give me an example of a time you had to learn a new skill or technology quickly.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to resolve a conflict between team members.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you went above and beyond what was expected of you.\\\"\\n        ]\\n\\n        random.shuffle(behavioral_questions)\\n        return random.sample(behavioral_questions, min(num_questions, len(behavioral_questions)))\\n\\n    def generate_follow_up_questions(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates follow-up questions based on the candidate's answer.\\n        This is a basic implementation and can be enhanced with NLP techniques.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        follow_up_questions = [\\n            \\\"Can you elaborate on that?\\\",\\n            \\\"Can you give me a specific example?\\\",\\n            \\\"What were the results of that?\\\",\\n            \\\"What was your role in that?\\\",\\n            \\\"What did you learn from that experience?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you measure the success of that project/task?\\\",\\n            \\\"What were the challenges you faced, and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            \\\"If you could do it again, what would you do differently?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you ensure quality in your work?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you collaborate with others on that?\\\"\\n        ]\\n\\n        random.shuffle(follow_up_questions)\\n        return random.sample(follow_up_questions, min(2, len(follow_up_questions)))\\n\\n    def generate_questions(self, num_technical_questions=5, num_behavioral_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates both technical and behavioral questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        technical_questions = self.generate_technical_questions(num_technical_questions)\\n        behavioral_questions = self.generate_behavioral_questions(num_behavioral_questions)\\n\\n        return {\\n            \\\"technical_questions\\\": technical_questions,\\n            \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": behavioral_questions\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    required_skills = [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Communication Skills\\\"]\\n    responsibilities = [\\\"Developing and maintaining web applications\\\", \\\"Writing clean, efficient code\\\", \\\"Collaborating with other developers\\\"]\\n    role_context = \\\"We are looking for a skilled Python Developer to join our team.\\\"\\n\\n    question_generator = QuestionGenerator(required_skills, responsibilities, role_context)\\n    questions = question_generator.generate_questions(num_technical_questions=3, num_behavioral_questions=3)\\n\\n    print(\\\"Technical Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in questions[\\\"technical_questions\\\"]:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in questions[\\\"behavioral_questions\\\"]:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n\\n    # Example of generating follow-up questions\\n    example_answer = \\\"I worked on a project where we had to migrate a legacy system to a new platform. It was challenging because the documentation was outdated and the team had limited experience with the new platform.\\\"\\n    follow_up_questions = question_generator.generate_follow_up_questions(example_answer)\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nFollow-up Questions based on the example answer:\\\")\\n    for question in follow_up_questions:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Implement Candidate Response Evaluation module to assess candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Interview Session module to present generated technical and behavioral questions to candidates, capture their responses, and store them for subsequent evaluation.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport datetime\\n\\nclass InterviewSession:\\n    def __init__(self, question_generator, candidate_name, job_title):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the InterviewSession with a question generator, candidate name, and job title.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.question_generator = question_generator\\n        self.candidate_name = candidate_name\\n        self.job_title = job_title\\n        self.interview_date = datetime.datetime.now().strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\\\")\\n        self.questions = {\\\"technical_questions\\\": [], \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": []}\\n        self.answers = {\\\"technical_answers\\\": {}, \\\"behavioral_answers\\\": {}}\\n        self.follow_up_questions = {}\\n        self.follow_up_answers = {}\\n\\n    def generate_interview_questions(self, num_technical_questions=5, num_behavioral_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical and behavioral questions using the question generator.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.questions = self.question_generator.generate_questions(num_technical_questions, num_behavioral_questions)\\n        return self.questions\\n\\n    def conduct_interview(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Conducts the interview by presenting questions and capturing candidate responses.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        print(f\\\"Interview for {self.candidate_name} - {self.job_title} - {self.interview_date}\\\")\\n        print(\\\"\\\\nTechnical Questions:\\\")\\n        for i, question in enumerate(self.questions[\\\"technical_questions\\\"]):\\n            print(f\\\"\\\\nQ{i + 1}: {question}\\\")\\n            answer = input(\\\"Candidate's Answer: \\\")\\n            self.answers[\\\"technical_answers\\\"][question] = answer\\n            self.generate_and_ask_follow_up(question, answer, \\\"technical\\\", i + 1)\\n\\n        print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Questions:\\\")\\n        for i, question in enumerate(self.questions[\\\"behavioral_questions\\\"]):\\n            print(f\\\"\\\\nQ{i + 1}: {question}\\\")\\n            answer = input(\\\"Candidate's Answer: \\\")\\n            self.answers[\\\"behavioral_answers\\\"][question] = answer\\n            self.generate_and_ask_follow_up(question, answer, \\\"behavioral\\\", i + 1)\\n\\n        print(\\\"\\\\nInterview completed. Thank you, {self.candidate_name}!\\\")\\n\\n    def generate_and_ask_follow_up(self, question, answer, question_type, question_number):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates follow-up questions based on the candidate's answer and captures their responses.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        follow_up_questions = self.question_generator.generate_follow_up_questions(answer)\\n        self.follow_up_questions[question] = follow_up_questions  # Store follow-up questions\\n\\n        print(\\\"\\\\nFollow-up Questions:\\\")\\n        follow_up_answers = {}\\n        for i, follow_up in enumerate(follow_up_questions):\\n            print(f\\\"  Follow-up Q{i + 1}: {follow_up}\\\")\\n            follow_up_answer = input(\\\"  Candidate's Answer: \\\")\\n            follow_up_answers[follow_up] = follow_up_answer\\n\\n        self.follow_up_answers[question] = follow_up_answers  # Store follow-up answers\\n\\n    def get_interview_data(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns all the interview data: questions, answers, and follow-up questions/answers.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return {\\n            \\\"candidate_name\\\": self.candidate_name,\\n            \\\"job_title\\\": self.job_title,\\n            \\\"interview_date\\\": self.interview_date,\\n            \\\"questions\\\": self.questions,\\n            \\\"answers\\\": self.answers,\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": self.follow_up_questions,\\n            \\\"follow_up_answers\\\": self.follow_up_answers\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    from task3 import QuestionGenerator  # Assuming task3.py is in the same directory\\n\\n    # Sample data for the QuestionGenerator\\n    required_skills = [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Communication Skills\\\"]\\n    responsibilities = [\\\"Developing and maintaining web applications\\\", \\\"Writing clean, efficient code\\\", \\\"Collaborating with other developers\\\"]\\n    role_context = \\\"We are looking for a skilled Python Developer to join our team.\\\"\\n\\n    # Initialize QuestionGenerator\\n    question_generator = QuestionGenerator(required_skills, responsibilities, role_context)\\n\\n    # Initialize InterviewSession\\n    candidate_name = \\\"John Doe\\\"\\n    job_title = \\\"Python Developer\\\"\\n    interview_session = InterviewSession(question_generator, candidate_name, job_title)\\n\\n    # Generate interview questions\\n    interview_session.generate_interview_questions(num_technical_questions=2, num_behavioral_questions=2)\\n\\n    # Conduct the interview (this will involve user input)\\n    interview_session.conduct_interview()\\n\\n    # Get all interview data\\n    interview_data = interview_session.get_interview_data()\\n\\n    # Print the interview data (for demonstration purposes)\\n    print(\\\"\\\\n--- Interview Data ---\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Candidate: {interview_data['candidate_name']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Job Title: {interview_data['job_title']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Interview Date: {interview_data['interview_date']}\\\")\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nTechnical Questions & Answers:\\\")\\n    for question, answer in interview_data[\\\"answers\\\"][\\\"technical_answers\\\"].items():\\n        print(f\\\"  Q: {question}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  A: {answer}\\\")\\n        if question in interview_data[\\\"follow_up_questions\\\"]:\\n            print(\\\"  Follow-up Questions & Answers:\\\")\\n            for f_question, f_answer in interview_data[\\\"follow_up_answers\\\"][question].items():\\n                print(f\\\"    FQ: {f_question}\\\")\\n                print(f\\\"    FA: {f_answer}\\\")\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Questions & Answers:\\\")\\n    for question, answer in interview_data[\\\"answers\\\"][\\\"behavioral_answers\\\"].items():\\n        print(f\\\"  Q: {question}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  A: {answer}\\\")\\n        if question in interview_data[\\\"follow_up_questions\\\"]:\\n            print(\\\"  Follow-up Questions & Answers:\\\")\\n            for f_question, f_answer in interview_data[\\\"follow_up_answers\\\"][question].items():\\n                print(f\\\"    FQ: {f_question}\\\")\\n                print(f\\\"    FA: {f_answer}\\\")\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:10:54.451297\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:10:56,189", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task6:\\n  Objective: Implement Evaluation Report Generator to compile match analysis, interview summary, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendations into a .txt report.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Follow-up Question Generation module to generate additional interview questions based on candidate responses and previous evaluation.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_questions, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on a candidate's response,\\n    previous questions asked, candidate profile, and job description.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response to the previous question.\\n        previous_questions (list): A list of questions already asked in the interview.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): A dictionary containing information about the candidate\\n                                  (e.g., skills, experience, education).\\n        job_description (str): The job description for the role.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of follow-up questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    follow_up_questions = []\\n\\n    # Analyze the candidate's response for keywords, skills, and areas of interest.\\n    keywords = extract_keywords(candidate_response)\\n    skills_mentioned = extract_skills(candidate_response)\\n    areas_of_interest = extract_interests(candidate_response)\\n\\n    # Identify any gaps or inconsistencies in the candidate's response.\\n    gaps = identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description)\\n    inconsistencies = identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile)\\n\\n    # Generate follow-up questions based on the analysis.\\n\\n    # 1. Probe Deeper into Specific Skills or Experiences:\\n    for skill in skills_mentioned:\\n        if f\\\"Tell me more about your experience with {skill}.\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Tell me more about your experience with {skill}.\\\")\\n        if f\\\"Can you provide a specific example of how you used {skill} to solve a problem?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n             follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Can you provide a specific example of how you used {skill} to solve a problem?\\\")\\n\\n    # 2. Explore Areas of Interest:\\n    for area in areas_of_interest:\\n        if f\\\"Why are you interested in {area}?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Why are you interested in {area}?\\\")\\n        if f\\\"How do you see your interest in {area} relating to this role?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"How do you see your interest in {area} relating to this role?\\\")\\n\\n    # 3. Address Gaps and Inconsistencies:\\n    for gap in gaps:\\n        if f\\\"Could you elaborate on {gap}?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Could you elaborate on {gap}?\\\")\\n\\n    for inconsistency in inconsistencies:\\n         if f\\\"I noticed that {inconsistency}. Can you clarify?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n              follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"I noticed that {inconsistency}. Can you clarify?\\\")\\n\\n    # 4. Ask Clarifying Questions:\\n    if \\\"clarify\\\" in keywords and \\\"not clear\\\" not in candidate_response.lower():\\n        follow_up_questions.append(\\\"Could you please clarify what you meant by that?\\\")\\n\\n    # 5. Behavioral Questions based on STAR method relative to the Job Description:\\n    jd_keywords = extract_keywords(job_description)\\n    for keyword in jd_keywords:\\n        if keyword in [\\\"problem-solving\\\", \\\"leadership\\\", \\\"teamwork\\\", \\\"communication\\\"] and f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {keyword}.\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n             follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {keyword}.\\\")\\n\\n    return follow_up_questions\\n\\n\\ndef extract_keywords(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts keywords from a given text.  This is a placeholder;\\n    a real implementation would use NLP techniques.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract keywords from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of keywords.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Simple placeholder implementation: split the text into words and return them as keywords.\\n    return text.lower().split()\\n\\n\\ndef extract_skills(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts skills from a given text. This is a placeholder;\\n    a real implementation would use a skills extraction model.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract skills from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of skills.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Placeholder implementation: returns a hardcoded list of skills if certain keywords are present\\n    skills = []\\n    if \\\"python\\\" in text.lower():\\n        skills.append(\\\"Python\\\")\\n    if \\\"java\\\" in text.lower():\\n        skills.append(\\\"Java\\\")\\n    if \\\"communication\\\" in text.lower():\\n        skills.append(\\\"Communication\\\")\\n    return skills\\n\\n\\ndef extract_interests(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts areas of interest from a given text. This is a placeholder;\\n    a real implementation would use topic modeling or similar techniques.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract interests from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of interests.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Placeholder implementation:  returns a hardcoded list if certain keywords are present\\n    interests = []\\n    if \\\"machine learning\\\" in text.lower():\\n        interests.append(\\\"Machine Learning\\\")\\n    if \\\"cloud computing\\\" in text.lower():\\n        interests.append(\\\"Cloud Computing\\\")\\n    return interests\\n\\n\\n\\ndef identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies gaps between the candidate's response, profile, and job description.\\n    This is a placeholder; a real implementation would compare required skills/experience\\n    from the job description with what's present in the candidate's profile and response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): The candidate's profile.\\n        job_description (str): The job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of identified gaps.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    gaps = []\\n    if \\\"experience with project management\\\" not in candidate_response.lower() and \\\"project management\\\" in job_description.lower():\\n        gaps.append(\\\"Experience with Project Management methodologies\\\")\\n    return gaps\\n\\n\\ndef identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies inconsistencies between the candidate's response and profile.\\n    This is a placeholder; a real implementation would compare claims made in the response\\n    with information provided in the candidate's resume/profile.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): The candidate's profile.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of identified inconsistencies.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    inconsistencies = []\\n    if \\\"lead a team of 10\\\" in candidate_response.lower() and candidate_profile.get(\\\"team_size_led\\\", 0) < 5:\\n        inconsistencies.append(\\\"Team size led inconsistent with profile\\\")\\n    return inconsistencies\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:10:56.189383\"\n}"}
