{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:11:12,475", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:11:12.475173\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement Follow-up Question Generation module to generate additional interview questions based on candidate responses and previous evaluation.\", \"result\": \"```python\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_questions, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on a candidate's response,\\n    previous questions asked, candidate profile, and job description.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response to the previous question.\\n        previous_questions (list): A list of questions already asked in the interview.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): A dictio...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The placeholder extraction functions are too simplistic and may not capture diverse skills, interests, or keywords from real text.  \\n2. We need richer follow-up question patterns: technical deep-dives (challenges, metrics, impact), behavioral probes (STAR components), and clarity questions for vague terms.  \\n3. We should avoid duplicates more robustly and ensure questions relate both to candidate responses and job requirements.  \\n4. The code should document clearly where it can be extended to integrate real NLP models or external libraries.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_questions, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on a candidate's response,\\n    history of asked questions, candidate profile, and job requirements.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's last response.\\n        previous_questions (list of str): Questions already asked.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate info, e.g. {'skills': [...], 'experience_years': X, ...}.\\n        job_description (str): Full text of the job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list of str: New follow-up questions (no duplicates of previous_questions).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Normalize\\n    prev = set(q.lower() for q in previous_questions)\\n    resp = candidate_response.strip()\\n    jd = job_description.lower()\\n\\n    # Extract concepts\\n    resp_skills = extract_skills(resp)\\n    resp_topics = extract_topics(resp)\\n    jd_skills = extract_skills(jd)\\n    gaps = identify_gaps(resp, candidate_profile, jd)\\n    inconsistencies = identify_inconsistencies(resp, candidate_profile)\\n\\n    follow_ups = []\\n\\n    # 1. Technical Deep Dive for each skill mentioned\\n    for skill in resp_skills:\\n        questions = [\\n            f\\\"Can you walk me through a specific project where you used {skill}? What were the main challenges and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            f\\\"What measurable impact did your work with {skill} have (e.g., performance improvements, cost savings)?\\\"\\n        ]\\n        for q in questions:\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 2. Align to Job-Required Skills not covered\\n    for skill in jd_skills:\\n        if skill not in resp_skills:\\n            q = f\\\"The JD emphasizes {skill}. Could you describe your experience with {skill}?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 3. Behavioral / STAR Probes for competency keywords\\n    competencies = [\\\"leadership\\\", \\\"teamwork\\\", \\\"problem-solving\\\", \\\"communication\\\", \\\"adaptability\\\"]\\n    for comp in competencies:\\n        if comp in jd:\\n            q = f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {comp}. What was the Situation, Task, Action, and Result?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 4. Clarify vague or high-level statements\\n    vague_phrases = [\\\"various\\\", \\\"multiple\\\", \\\"significant\\\", \\\"extensive\\\"]\\n    for phrase in vague_phrases:\\n        if phrase in resp.lower():\\n            q = f\\\"You mentioned '{phrase}'. Could you give specific examples or metrics to illustrate that?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n            break  # only one such question\\n\\n    # 5. Address identified gaps\\n    for gap in gaps:\\n        q = f\\\"I noticed a gap: {gap}. Could you elaborate on this area?\\\"\\n        if q.lower() not in prev:\\n            follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 6. Query inconsistencies\\n    for inc in inconsistencies:\\n        q = f\\\"I saw a discrepancy: {inc}. Can you help me reconcile this?\\\"\\n        if q.lower() not in prev:\\n            follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    return follow_ups\\n\\n\\ndef extract_skills(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    A simple regex-based placeholder that finds capitalized words or common tech terms.\\n    Replace with NLP model or skills ontology in production.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    tech_terms = ['python', 'java', 'c++', 'aws', 'docker', 'kubernetes', 'sql', 'javascript']\\n    found = set()\\n    # match capitalized words (e.g., React, Django)\\n    for match in re.findall(r'\\\\b[A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9+\\\\-#]+\\\\b', text):\\n        found.add(match)\\n    # match known tech terms\\n    for term in tech_terms:\\n        if term in text.lower():\\n            found.add(term.title())\\n    return list(found)\\n\\n\\ndef extract_topics(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Placeholder: identify multi-word interest areas by common phrases.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    topics = []\\n    patterns = {\\n        'machine learning': r'machine learning',\\n        'cloud computing': r'cloud computing',\\n        'data engineering': r'data engineering',\\n        'project management': r'project management',\\n    }\\n    for name, pat in patterns.items():\\n        if re.search(pat, text, flags=re.I):\\n            topics.append(name.title())\\n    return topics\\n\\n\\ndef identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Compare JD skills vs. response/profile. Highlight missing areas.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    gaps = []\\n    jd_skills = set(extract_skills(job_description.lower()))\\n    profile_skills = set(s.lower() for s in candidate_profile.get('skills', []))\\n    resp_skills = set(s.lower() for s in extract_skills(candidate_response))\\n    missing = jd_skills - (profile_skills | resp_skills)\\n    for skill in missing:\\n        gaps.append(f\\\"{skill} experience\\\")\\n    return gaps\\n\\n\\ndef identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Flag contradictions, e.g. team size statements vs. profile.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    inc = []\\n    # example: candidate said 'led a team of X' but profile says different\\n    m = re.search(r'led a team of (\\\\d+)', candidate_response.lower())\\n    if m:\\n        claimed = int(m.group(1))\\n        actual = candidate_profile.get('team_size_led', 0)\\n        if claimed != actual:\\n            inc.append(f\\\"Claimed leading a team of {claimed} vs profile's {actual}\\\")\\n    return inc\\n```\\n\\nExplanation of improvements:\\n- Richer question templates: deep-dives with challenges and metrics.\\n- Aligns directly to JD-required skills not yet addressed.\\n- STAR behavioral probes explicitly include Situation, Task, Action, Result.\\n- Clarifies vague language with examples or metrics.\\n- More robust duplicate-check (lowercased set).\\n- Well-documented placeholders for future NLP model integration.\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:11:22,922", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Implement Follow-up \",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 2,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```python\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_questions, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on a candidate's response,\\n    previous questions asked, candidate profile, and job description.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response to the previous question.\\n        previous_questions (list): A list of questions already asked in the interview.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): A dictionary containing information about the candidate\\n                                  (e.g., skills, experience, education).\\n        job_description (str): The job description for the role.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of follow-up questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    follow_up_questions = []\\n\\n    # Analyze the candidate's response for keywords, skills, and areas of interest.\\n    keywords = extract_keywords(candidate_response)\\n    skills_mentioned = extract_skills(candidate_response)\\n    areas_of_interest = extract_interests(candidate_response)\\n\\n    # Identify any gaps or inconsistencies in the candidate's response.\\n    gaps = identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description)\\n    inconsistencies = identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile)\\n\\n    # Generate follow-up questions based on the analysis.\\n\\n    # 1. Probe Deeper into Specific Skills or Experiences:\\n    for skill in skills_mentioned:\\n        if f\\\"Tell me more about your experience with {skill}.\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Tell me more about your experience with {skill}.\\\")\\n        if f\\\"Can you provide a specific example of how you used {skill} to solve a problem?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n             follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Can you provide a specific example of how you used {skill} to solve a problem?\\\")\\n\\n    # 2. Explore Areas of Interest:\\n    for area in areas_of_interest:\\n        if f\\\"Why are you interested in {area}?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Why are you interested in {area}?\\\")\\n        if f\\\"How do you see your interest in {area} relating to this role?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"How do you see your interest in {area} relating to this role?\\\")\\n\\n    # 3. Address Gaps and Inconsistencies:\\n    for gap in gaps:\\n        if f\\\"Could you elaborate on {gap}?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Could you elaborate on {gap}?\\\")\\n\\n    for inconsistency in inconsistencies:\\n         if f\\\"I noticed that {inconsistency}. Can you clarify?\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n              follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"I noticed that {inconsistency}. Can you clarify?\\\")\\n\\n    # 4. Ask Clarifying Questions:\\n    if \\\"clarify\\\" in keywords and \\\"not clear\\\" not in candidate_response.lower():\\n        follow_up_questions.append(\\\"Could you please clarify what you meant by that?\\\")\\n\\n    # 5. Behavioral Questions based on STAR method relative to the Job Description:\\n    jd_keywords = extract_keywords(job_description)\\n    for keyword in jd_keywords:\\n        if keyword in [\\\"problem-solving\\\", \\\"leadership\\\", \\\"teamwork\\\", \\\"communication\\\"] and f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {keyword}.\\\" not in previous_questions:\\n             follow_up_questions.append(f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {keyword}.\\\")\\n\\n    return follow_up_questions\\n\\n\\ndef extract_keywords(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts keywords from a given text.  This is a placeholder;\\n    a real implementation would use NLP techniques.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract keywords from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of keywords.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Simple placeholder implementation: split the text into words and return them as keywords.\\n    return text.lower().split()\\n\\n\\ndef extract_skills(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts skills from a given text. This is a placeholder;\\n    a real implementation would use a skills extraction model.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract skills from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of skills.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Placeholder implementation: returns a hardcoded list of skills if certain keywords are present\\n    skills = []\\n    if \\\"python\\\" in text.lower():\\n        skills.append(\\\"Python\\\")\\n    if \\\"java\\\" in text.lower():\\n        skills.append(\\\"Java\\\")\\n    if \\\"communication\\\" in text.lower():\\n        skills.append(\\\"Communication\\\")\\n    return skills\\n\\n\\ndef extract_interests(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts areas of interest from a given text. This is a placeholder;\\n    a real implementation would use topic modeling or similar techniques.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract interests from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of interests.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Placeholder implementation:  returns a hardcoded list if certain keywords are present\\n    interests = []\\n    if \\\"machine learning\\\" in text.lower():\\n        interests.append(\\\"Machine Learning\\\")\\n    if \\\"cloud computing\\\" in text.lower():\\n        interests.append(\\\"Cloud Computing\\\")\\n    return interests\\n\\n\\n\\ndef identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies gaps between the candidate's response, profile, and job description.\\n    This is a placeholder; a real implementation would compare required skills/experience\\n    from the job description with what's present in the candidate's profile and response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): The candidate's profile.\\n        job_description (str): The job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of identified gaps.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    gaps = []\\n    if \\\"experience with project management\\\" not in candidate_response.lower() and \\\"project management\\\" in job_description.lower():\\n        gaps.append(\\\"Experience with Project Management methodologies\\\")\\n    return gaps\\n\\n\\ndef identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies inconsistencies between the candidate's response and profile.\\n    This is a placeholder; a real implementation would compare claims made in the response\\n    with information provided in the candidate's resume/profile.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): The candidate's profile.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of identified inconsistencies.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    inconsistencies = []\\n    if \\\"lead a team of 10\\\" in candidate_response.lower() and candidate_profile.get(\\\"team_size_led\\\", 0) < 5:\\n        inconsistencies.append(\\\"Team size led inconsistent with profile\\\")\\n    return inconsistencies\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n1. The placeholder extraction functions are too simplistic and may not capture diverse skills, interests, or keywords from real text.  \\n2. We need richer follow-up question patterns: technical deep-dives (challenges, metrics, impact), behavioral probes (STAR components), and clarity questions for vague terms.  \\n3. We should avoid duplicates more robustly and ensure questions relate both to candidate responses and job requirements.  \\n4. The code should document clearly where it can be extended to integrate real NLP models or external libraries.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_questions, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on a candidate's response,\\n    history of asked questions, candidate profile, and job requirements.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's last response.\\n        previous_questions (list of str): Questions already asked.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate info, e.g. {'skills': [...], 'experience_years': X, ...}.\\n        job_description (str): Full text of the job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list of str: New follow-up questions (no duplicates of previous_questions).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Normalize\\n    prev = set(q.lower() for q in previous_questions)\\n    resp = candidate_response.strip()\\n    jd = job_description.lower()\\n\\n    # Extract concepts\\n    resp_skills = extract_skills(resp)\\n    resp_topics = extract_topics(resp)\\n    jd_skills = extract_skills(jd)\\n    gaps = identify_gaps(resp, candidate_profile, jd)\\n    inconsistencies = identify_inconsistencies(resp, candidate_profile)\\n\\n    follow_ups = []\\n\\n    # 1. Technical Deep Dive for each skill mentioned\\n    for skill in resp_skills:\\n        questions = [\\n            f\\\"Can you walk me through a specific project where you used {skill}? What were the main challenges and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            f\\\"What measurable impact did your work with {skill} have (e.g., performance improvements, cost savings)?\\\"\\n        ]\\n        for q in questions:\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 2. Align to Job-Required Skills not covered\\n    for skill in jd_skills:\\n        if skill not in resp_skills:\\n            q = f\\\"The JD emphasizes {skill}. Could you describe your experience with {skill}?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 3. Behavioral / STAR Probes for competency keywords\\n    competencies = [\\\"leadership\\\", \\\"teamwork\\\", \\\"problem-solving\\\", \\\"communication\\\", \\\"adaptability\\\"]\\n    for comp in competencies:\\n        if comp in jd:\\n            q = f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {comp}. What was the Situation, Task, Action, and Result?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 4. Clarify vague or high-level statements\\n    vague_phrases = [\\\"various\\\", \\\"multiple\\\", \\\"significant\\\", \\\"extensive\\\"]\\n    for phrase in vague_phrases:\\n        if phrase in resp.lower():\\n            q = f\\\"You mentioned '{phrase}'. Could you give specific examples or metrics to illustrate that?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n            break  # only one such question\\n\\n    # 5. Address identified gaps\\n    for gap in gaps:\\n        q = f\\\"I noticed a gap: {gap}. Could you elaborate on this area?\\\"\\n        if q.lower() not in prev:\\n            follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 6. Query inconsistencies\\n    for inc in inconsistencies:\\n        q = f\\\"I saw a discrepancy: {inc}. Can you help me reconcile this?\\\"\\n        if q.lower() not in prev:\\n            follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    return follow_ups\\n\\n\\ndef extract_skills(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    A simple regex-based placeholder that finds capitalized words or common tech terms.\\n    Replace with NLP model or skills ontology in production.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    tech_terms = ['python', 'java', 'c++', 'aws', 'docker', 'kubernetes', 'sql', 'javascript']\\n    found = set()\\n    # match capitalized words (e.g., React, Django)\\n    for match in re.findall(r'\\\\b[A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9+\\\\-#]+\\\\b', text):\\n        found.add(match)\\n    # match known tech terms\\n    for term in tech_terms:\\n        if term in text.lower():\\n            found.add(term.title())\\n    return list(found)\\n\\n\\ndef extract_topics(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Placeholder: identify multi-word interest areas by common phrases.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    topics = []\\n    patterns = {\\n        'machine learning': r'machine learning',\\n        'cloud computing': r'cloud computing',\\n        'data engineering': r'data engineering',\\n        'project management': r'project management',\\n    }\\n    for name, pat in patterns.items():\\n        if re.search(pat, text, flags=re.I):\\n            topics.append(name.title())\\n    return topics\\n\\n\\ndef identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Compare JD skills vs. response/profile. Highlight missing areas.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    gaps = []\\n    jd_skills = set(extract_skills(job_description.lower()))\\n    profile_skills = set(s.lower() for s in candidate_profile.get('skills', []))\\n    resp_skills = set(s.lower() for s in extract_skills(candidate_response))\\n    missing = jd_skills - (profile_skills | resp_skills)\\n    for skill in missing:\\n        gaps.append(f\\\"{skill} experience\\\")\\n    return gaps\\n\\n\\ndef identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Flag contradictions, e.g. team size statements vs. profile.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    inc = []\\n    # example: candidate said 'led a team of X' but profile says different\\n    m = re.search(r'led a team of (\\\\d+)', candidate_response.lower())\\n    if m:\\n        claimed = int(m.group(1))\\n        actual = candidate_profile.get('team_size_led', 0)\\n        if claimed != actual:\\n            inc.append(f\\\"Claimed leading a team of {claimed} vs profile's {actual}\\\")\\n    return inc\\n```\\n\\nExplanation of improvements:\\n- Richer question templates: deep-dives with challenges and metrics.\\n- Aligns directly to JD-required skills not yet addressed.\\n- STAR behavioral probes explicitly include Situation, Task, Action, Result.\\n- Clarifies vague language with examples or metrics.\\n- More robust duplicate-check (lowercased set).\\n- Well-documented placeholders for future NLP model integration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- 