{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:12:34,190", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:12:34.190371\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Develop Scoring Engine to aggregate match analysis and response evaluation into category scores across evaluation criteria.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nclass ScoringEngine:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Aggregates match analysis and response evaluations to generate category scores\\n    across various evaluation criteria.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, match_analysis, interview_evaluations):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the ScoringEngine with match analysis and interview evaluations.\\n\\n        :param match_analysis: Dictionary containing the match analysis report.\\n        :param interview_evaluations: Dictionary containing the interview evaluations.\\n ...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. Question‐type detection relies on keywords in the question string (e.g. “technical”, “behavioral”), which is brittle. It’s better to add an explicit `type` field in each evaluation entry.\\n2. Only `skill_match` is used from `match_analysis`; other match categories (experience, education, overall) are ignored. We should include a `calculate_match_score` method (e.g. using `overall_match`) and expose it in the breakdown.\\n3. The overall‐score weights don’t account for the match score. We should add a `match_weight` parameter so users can tune how much resume‐job fit contributes to the final score.\\n4. Adjusted sample data to include `\\\"type\\\": \\\"technical\\\"` or `\\\"behavioral\\\"` fields so the engine can correctly classify questions.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nclass ScoringEngine:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Aggregates match analysis and response evaluations into category scores\\n    across various evaluation criteria.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, match_analysis, interview_evaluations):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :param match_analysis: dict containing the match analysis report.\\n            Expected keys: 'skill_match', 'experience_match', 'education_match', 'overall_match'\\n            with numeric 'score' or boolean 'matched' fields.\\n        :param interview_evaluations: dict mapping question -> evaluation dict.\\n            Each evaluation must include:\\n                - type: 'technical' or 'behavioral'\\n                - relevance (0–5), depth (0–5), confidence (0–5)\\n                - technical_accuracy (0–5) for technical questions\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.match_analysis = match_analysis\\n        self.interview_evaluations = interview_evaluations\\n\\n    def calculate_match_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates the resume-job match score based on overall_match.\\n        :return: Match score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        overall = self.match_analysis.get(\\\"overall_match\\\", {}).get(\\\"score\\\", 0.0)\\n        return overall * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_technical_skill_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Combines skill_match (from match_analysis) and average technical_accuracy.\\n        :return: Technical skill score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        w_skill = 0.5\\n        w_interview = 0.5\\n\\n        # 0–1\\n        skill_match = self.match_analysis.get(\\\"skill_match\\\", {}).get(\\\"score\\\", 0.0)\\n\\n        # gather technical_accuracy from entries labeled as 'technical'\\n        tech_scores = []\\n        for eval in self.interview_evaluations.values():\\n            if eval.get(\\\"type\\\") == \\\"technical\\\":\\n                tech_scores.append(eval.get(\\\"technical_accuracy\\\", 0))\\n\\n        if tech_scores:\\n            avg_tech = sum(tech_scores) / len(tech_scores)  # 0–5\\n            avg_tech /= 5.0  # scale to 0–1\\n        else:\\n            avg_tech = 0.0\\n\\n        combined = w_skill * skill_match + w_interview * avg_tech\\n        return combined * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_problem_solving_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Uses depth and relevance of behavioral questions about problem-solving.\\n        :return: Problem-solving score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        scores = []\\n        for eval in self.interview_evaluations.values():\\n            if eval.get(\\\"type\\\") == \\\"behavioral\\\":\\n                # depth * relevance, max product = 25\\n                scores.append(eval.get(\\\"depth\\\", 0) * eval.get(\\\"relevance\\\", 0))\\n\\n        if not scores:\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n        avg = sum(scores) / len(scores)  # 0–25\\n        return (avg / 25.0) * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_communication_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Uses confidence and relevance across all questions.\\n        :return: Communication score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        scores = []\\n        for eval in self.interview_evaluations.values():\\n            # apply to all types\\n            scores.append(eval.get(\\\"confidence\\\", 0) * eval.get(\\\"relevance\\\", 0))\\n\\n        if not scores:\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n        avg = sum(scores) / len(scores)  # 0–25\\n        return (avg / 25.0) * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_overall_score(\\n        self,\\n        match_weight=0.2,\\n        technical_weight=0.4,\\n        problem_solving_weight=0.2,\\n        communication_weight=0.2\\n    ):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Weighted combination of match, technical, problem-solving, and communication.\\n        Weights must sum to 1.0.\\n        :return: Overall score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # validate sum of weights\\n        total_w = match_weight + technical_weight + problem_solving_weight + communication_weight\\n        if abs(total_w - 1.0) > 1e-6:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\\"Weights must sum to 1.0, got {total_w}\\\")\\n\\n        m = self.calculate_match_score()\\n        t = self.calculate_technical_skill_score()\\n        p = self.calculate_problem_solving_score()\\n        c = self.calculate_communication_score()\\n\\n        overall = (\\n            match_weight * m +\\n            technical_weight * t +\\n            problem_solving_weight * p +\\n            communication_weight * c\\n        )\\n        return overall\\n\\n    def get_scoring_breakdown(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :return: dict with detailed scores for each category and overall.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        breakdown = {\\n            \\\"match\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_match_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Resume-job match score: {self.calculate_match_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"technical_skills\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_technical_skill_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Technical score: {self.calculate_technical_skill_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"problem_solving\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_problem_solving_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Problem-solving score: {self.calculate_problem_solving_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"communication\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_communication_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Communication score: {self.calculate_communication_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"overall\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_overall_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Overall score: {self.calculate_overall_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return breakdown\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Example usage with explicit 'type' fields:\\n    match_analysis = {\\n        \\\"skill_match\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 0.8},\\n        \\\"experience_match\\\": {\\\"matched\\\": True},\\n        \\\"education_match\\\": {\\\"matched\\\": True},\\n        \\\"overall_match\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 0.85}\\n    }\\n    interview_evaluations = {\\n        \\\"What is a decorator in Python?\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"technical\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5, \\\"depth\\\": 4, \\\"confidence\\\": 4, \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 5\\n        },\\n        \\\"Explain lists vs. tuples in Python.\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"technical\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5, \\\"depth\\\": 3, \\\"confidence\\\": 4, \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 4\\n        },\\n        \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"behavioral\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 4, \\\"depth\\\": 3, \\\"confidence\\\": 4\\n        },\\n        \\\"Describe working with a difficult team member.\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"behavioral\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5, \\\"depth\\\": 4, \\\"confidence\\\": 3\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    engine = ScoringEngine(match_analysis, interview_evaluations)\\n    breakdown = engine.get_scoring_breakdown()\\n    print(breakdown)\\n```\"}"}
