{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:13:03,581", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n\\nYou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop Match Analyzer module to compare parsed resume data against job requirements and compute a resume-job match score with analysis.\\n  Result: ```python\\nclass MatchAnalyzer:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Analyzes the match between a job description and a resume based on extracted information.\\n    Calculates a match score and provides a detailed analysis of the match.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_data, resume_data):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the MatchAnalyzer with job description and resume data.\\n\\n        :param job_description_data: Dictionary containing job description information (skills, responsibilities, etc.).\\n        :param resume_data: Dictionary containing resume information (skills, experience, education, etc.).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description_data = job_description_data\\n        self.resume_data = resume_data\\n\\n    def calculate_skill_match_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates a skill match score based on the overlap between required skills and resume skills.\\n\\n        :return: Skill match score (float between 0 and 1).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        required_skills = set(map(str.lower, self.job_description_data.get(\\\"required_skills\\\", [])))\\n        resume_skills = set(map(str.lower, self.resume_data.get(\\\"skills\\\", [])))\\n\\n        if not required_skills:\\n            return 1.0  # If no required skills are specified, consider it a perfect match.\\n\\n        matched_skills = required_skills.intersection(resume_skills)\\n        skill_match_score = len(matched_skills) / len(required_skills)\\n        return skill_match_score\\n\\n    def analyze_experience_match(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Analyzes the experience match between the job description and the resume.  This is a simplified\\n        implementation.  A more robust implementation would consider the relevance of the experience to the role.\\n\\n        :return: A dictionary containing analysis of experience match (bool matched, str details).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        job_responsibilities = self.job_description_data.get(\\\"responsibilities\\\", [])\\n        resume_experience = self.resume_data.get(\\\"experience\\\", [])\\n\\n        matched = False\\n        details = \\\"No significant experience match found.\\\"\\n\\n        for responsibility in job_responsibilities:\\n            for experience in resume_experience:\\n                if experience.get(\\\"details\\\") and any(responsibility.lower() in detail.lower() for detail in experience.get(\\\"details\\\")):\\n                    matched = True\\n                    details = \\\"Experience found matching job responsibilities.\\\"\\n                    break\\n            if matched:\\n                break\\n\\n        return {\\\"matched\\\": matched, \\\"details\\\": details}\\n\\n    def analyze_education_match(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Analyzes the education match between the job description and the resume.  This is a simplified\\n        implementation.\\n\\n        :return: A dictionary containing analysis of education match (bool matched, str details).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # In a real-world scenario, this could compare degrees, institutions, etc.\\n        # For simplicity, this example always returns a match.\\n        return {\\\"matched\\\": True, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Education requirements met.\\\"}\\n\\n\\n    def calculate_overall_match_score(self, skill_weight=0.6, experience_weight=0.3, education_weight=0.1):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates an overall match score based on weighted combination of skill, experience and education matches.\\n\\n        :param skill_weight: Weight for skill match score.\\n        :param experience_weight: Weight for experience match score.\\n        :param education_weight: Weight for education match score.\\n        :return: Overall match score (float between 0 and 1).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        skill_match_score = self.calculate_skill_match_score()\\n        experience_match = self.analyze_experience_match()\\n        education_match = self.analyze_education_match()\\n\\n        experience_score = 1.0 if experience_match[\\\"matched\\\"] else 0.0\\n        education_score = 1.0 if education_match[\\\"matched\\\"] else 0.0\\n\\n        overall_match_score = (\\n            skill_weight * skill_match_score +\\n            experience_weight * experience_score +\\n            education_weight * education_score\\n        )\\n\\n        return overall_match_score\\n\\n    def get_match_analysis(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a comprehensive match analysis report.\\n\\n        :return: A dictionary containing the match analysis report.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        skill_match_score = self.calculate_skill_match_score()\\n        experience_match = self.analyze_experience_match()\\n        education_match = self.analyze_education_match()\\n        overall_match_score = self.calculate_overall_match_score()\\n\\n        analysis_report = {\\n            \\\"skill_match\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": skill_match_score,\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Skill match score: {skill_match_score:.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"experience_match\\\": {\\n                \\\"matched\\\": experience_match[\\\"matched\\\"],\\n                \\\"details\\\": experience_match[\\\"details\\\"]\\n            },\\n            \\\"education_match\\\": {\\n                \\\"matched\\\": education_match[\\\"matched\\\"],\\n                \\\"details\\\": education_match[\\\"details\\\"]\\n            },\\n            \\\"overall_match\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": overall_match_score,\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Overall match score: {overall_match_score:.2f}\\\"\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return analysis_report\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage:\\n    job_description_data = {\\n        \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Communication Skills\\\"],\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\\"developing and maintaining web applications\\\", \\\"writing clean, efficient code\\\", \\\"designing and implementing new features\\\"]\\n    }\\n\\n    resume_data = {\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Java\\\", \\\"JavaScript\\\", \\\"AWS\\\", \\\"Docker\\\", \\\"SQL\\\"],\\n        \\\"experience\\\": [\\n            {\\n                \\\"title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n                \\\"company\\\": \\\"ABC Company\\\",\\n                \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"2018\\\",\\n                \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"2023\\\",\\n                \\\"details\\\": [\\\"Developed web apps in Python\\\", \\\"Deployed with Docker\\\"]\\n            },\\n            {\\n                \\\"title\\\": \\\"Software Developer\\\",\\n                \\\"company\\\": \\\"XYZ Company\\\",\\n                \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"2016\\\",\\n                \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"2018\\\",\\n                \\\"details\\\": [\\\"Built REST APIs\\\"]\\n            }\\n        ],\\n        \\\"education\\\": [\\n            {\\n                \\\"degree\\\": \\\"Bachelor of Science in Computer Science\\\",\\n                \\\"institution\\\": \\\"University of California\\\",\\n                \\\"year\\\": \\\"2016\\\"\\n            }\\n        ]\\n    }\\n\\n    analyzer = MatchAnalyzer(job_description_data, resume_data)\\n    analysis_report = analyzer.get_match_analysis()\\n\\n    print(analysis_report)\\n```\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Build Question Generation Engine to produce technical and behavioral interview questions based on extracted job requirements.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass QuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, required_skills, responsibilities, role_context):\\n        self.required_skills = required_skills\\n        self.responsibilities = responsibilities\\n        self.role_context = role_context\\n\\n    def generate_technical_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical interview questions based on the required skills.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        technical_questions = []\\n        if \\\"Python\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of decorators in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the Global Interpreter Lock (GIL) in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"How does memory management work in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the concept of inheritance and polymorphism in Python.\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"Java\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between == and .equals() in Java.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the principles of object-oriented programming in Java?\\\",\\n                \\\"How does garbage collection work in Java?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of interfaces and abstract classes in Java.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the different types of exceptions in Java?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"JavaScript\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between let, const, and var in JavaScript.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of the 'this' keyword in JavaScript?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the concept of closures in JavaScript.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does prototypal inheritance work in JavaScript?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the advantages of using arrow functions in JavaScript?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"SQL\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of using indexes in a database?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of stored procedures in SQL.\\\",\\n                \\\"How can you optimize a slow-running SQL query?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are ACID properties in the context of databases?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"AWS\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between EC2 and Lambda in AWS.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does S3 work and what are its use cases?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the purpose of IAM in AWS.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the difference between VPC and subnet in AWS?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you monitor and manage application performance in AWS?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"Docker\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"What is Docker and why is it used?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between Docker images and containers.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you create a Dockerfile?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage Docker volumes?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the advantages of using Docker Compose?\\\"\\n            ])\\n        if \\\"Kubernetes\\\" in self.required_skills:\\n            technical_questions.extend([\\n                \\\"What is Kubernetes and why is it used?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between Pods, Deployments, and Services in Kubernetes.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage Kubernetes deployments?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you scale applications in Kubernetes?\\\",\\n                \\\"What are Kubernetes namespaces?\\\"\\n            ])\\n\\n        random.shuffle(technical_questions)\\n        return random.sample(technical_questions, min(num_questions, len(technical_questions)))\\n\\n    def generate_behavioral_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates behavioral interview questions based on the responsibilities and role context.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        behavioral_questions = [\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you had to work under pressure to meet a deadline.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to deal with a difficult team member. How did you handle it?\\\",\\n            \\\"Give me an example of a time you had to make a decision with incomplete information.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you failed. What did you learn from it?\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to adapt to a significant change in your work environment.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you had to convince a team to do something in a new way.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a time when you anticipated potential problems and took measures to prevent them.\\\",\\n            \\\"Give me an example of a time you had to learn a new skill or technology quickly.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where you had to resolve a conflict between team members.\\\",\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you went above and beyond what was expected of you.\\\"\\n        ]\\n\\n        random.shuffle(behavioral_questions)\\n        return random.sample(behavioral_questions, min(num_questions, len(behavioral_questions)))\\n\\n    def generate_follow_up_questions(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates follow-up questions based on the candidate's answer.\\n        This is a basic implementation and can be enhanced with NLP techniques.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        follow_up_questions = [\\n            \\\"Can you elaborate on that?\\\",\\n            \\\"Can you give me a specific example?\\\",\\n            \\\"What were the results of that?\\\",\\n            \\\"What was your role in that?\\\",\\n            \\\"What did you learn from that experience?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you measure the success of that project/task?\\\",\\n            \\\"What were the challenges you faced, and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            \\\"If you could do it again, what would you do differently?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you ensure quality in your work?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you collaborate with others on that?\\\"\\n        ]\\n\\n        random.shuffle(follow_up_questions)\\n        return random.sample(follow_up_questions, min(2, len(follow_up_questions)))\\n\\n    def generate_questions(self, num_technical_questions=5, num_behavioral_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates both technical and behavioral questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        technical_questions = self.generate_technical_questions(num_technical_questions)\\n        behavioral_questions = self.generate_behavioral_questions(num_behavioral_questions)\\n\\n        return {\\n            \\\"technical_questions\\\": technical_questions,\\n            \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": behavioral_questions\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    required_skills = [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"React\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Communication Skills\\\"]\\n    responsibilities = [\\\"Developing and maintaining web applications\\\", \\\"Writing clean, efficient code\\\", \\\"Collaborating with other developers\\\"]\\n    role_context = \\\"We are looking for a skilled Python Developer to join our team.\\\"\\n\\n    question_generator = QuestionGenerator(required_skills, responsibilities, role_context)\\n    questions = question_generator.generate_questions(num_technical_questions=3, num_behavioral_questions=3)\\n\\n    print(\\\"Technical Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in questions[\\\"technical_questions\\\"]:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in questions[\\\"behavioral_questions\\\"]:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n\\n    # Example of generating follow-up questions\\n    example_answer = \\\"I worked on a project where we had to migrate a legacy system to a new platform. It was challenging because the documentation was outdated and the team had limited experience with the new platform.\\\"\\n    follow_up_questions = question_generator.generate_follow_up_questions(example_answer)\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nFollow-up Questions based on the example answer:\\\")\\n    for question in follow_up_questions:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n```\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Implement Candidate Response Evaluation module to assess candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n  Result: ```python\\nclass CandidateResponseEvaluator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates candidate responses based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, job_description, candidate_resume):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the CandidateResponseEvaluator with the job description and candidate resume.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description = job_description\\n        self.candidate_resume = candidate_resume\\n\\n    def evaluate_response(self, question, answer, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates a single candidate response.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            question_type (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing the evaluation scores and feedback.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        evaluation = {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": self.evaluate_relevance(question, answer),\\n            \\\"depth\\\": self.evaluate_depth(answer, question_type),\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": self.evaluate_confidence(answer),\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": self.evaluate_technical_accuracy(question, answer, question_type),\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": self.generate_feedback(question, answer, question_type)\\n        }\\n        return evaluation\\n\\n    def evaluate_relevance(self, question, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the relevance of the answer to the question.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: A score between 1 and 5 (1 being not relevant, 5 being highly relevant).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation.  A more sophisticated implementation might use NLP techniques\\n        # to compare the similarity between the question and the answer.\\n        if not answer:\\n            return 1  # No answer, not relevant\\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\\n\\n        common_keywords = set(keywords_in_question) & set(keywords_in_answer)\\n\\n        if len(common_keywords) > 0:\\n            return 4\\n        else:\\n            return 3\\n\\n    def evaluate_depth(self, answer, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the depth of the answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: A score between 1 and 5 (1 being superficial, 5 being very in-depth).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation.  A more sophisticated implementation might consider\\n        # the length of the answer, the level of detail provided, and the use of examples.\\n        if not answer:\\n            return 1\\n\\n        word_count = len(answer.split())\\n\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n            if word_count > 100:\\n                return 5\\n            elif word_count > 50:\\n                return 4\\n            else:\\n                return 3\\n        else:  # Behavioral\\n            if word_count > 150:\\n                return 5\\n            elif word_count > 75:\\n                return 4\\n            else:\\n                return 3\\n\\n    def evaluate_confidence(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the candidate's confidence level based on the answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: A score between 1 and 5 (1 being not confident, 5 being very confident).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation.  This could be improved by analyzing the language used\\n        # in the answer for hesitation words, qualifiers, and assertive statements.\\n        if not answer:\\n            return 1\\n\\n        # Simple check for hesitation words.\\n        hesitation_words = [\\\"I think\\\", \\\"I believe\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"probably\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\"]\\n        answer_lower = answer.lower()\\n        hesitation_count = sum([1 for word in hesitation_words if word in answer_lower])\\n\\n        if hesitation_count > 2:\\n            return 2\\n        elif hesitation_count > 0:\\n            return 3\\n        else:\\n            return 4\\n\\n    def evaluate_technical_accuracy(self, question, answer, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the technical accuracy of the answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: A score between 1 and 5 (1 being inaccurate, 5 being highly accurate).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation. This requires domain-specific knowledge and potentially\\n        # access to external knowledge bases or APIs to verify the accuracy of the information provided.\\n        # This is a simplified example and should be replaced with a more robust implementation.\\n        if question_type != \\\"technical\\\":\\n            return 5  # Not applicable for behavioral questions\\n\\n        if not answer:\\n            return 1\\n\\n        # Very basic keyword check as an example.  Replace with actual technical validation.\\n        if \\\"python\\\" in question.lower() and \\\"python\\\" in answer.lower():\\n            return 4\\n        else:\\n            return 3\\n\\n    def generate_feedback(self, question, answer, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates feedback based on the evaluation.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            str: Feedback on the candidate's response.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation.  This could be improved by providing more specific feedback\\n        # based on the individual scores for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n        if not answer:\\n            return \\\"The candidate did not provide an answer.\\\"\\n\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n            return \\\"The candidate's answer was relevant and demonstrated some technical knowledge.\\\"\\n        else:\\n            return \\\"The candidate's answer was relevant to the behavioral question.\\\"\\n\\n    def evaluate_interview(self, interview_data):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the entire interview based on the provided interview data.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            interview_data (dict): A dictionary containing the interview data (questions, answers).\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing the evaluation results for each question.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        evaluations = {}\\n        for question_type in [\\\"technical_questions\\\", \\\"behavioral_questions\\\"]:\\n            for i, question in enumerate(interview_data[\\\"questions\\\"][question_type]):\\n                if question in interview_data[\\\"answers\\\"][question_type.replace(\\\"_questions\\\", \\\"_answers\\\")]:\\n                    answer = interview_data[\\\"answers\\\"][question_type.replace(\\\"_questions\\\", \\\"_answers\\\")][question]\\n                else:\\n                    answer = \\\"\\\"\\n\\n                evaluations[question] = self.evaluate_response(question, answer, question_type[:-10])\\n        return evaluations\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage:\\n    job_description = \\\"We are looking for a Python developer with experience in web development.\\\"\\n    candidate_resume = \\\"I am a Python developer with 5 years of experience.\\\"\\n\\n    evaluator = CandidateResponseEvaluator(job_description, candidate_resume)\\n\\n    # Sample Interview Data (replace with actual data from the InterviewSession)\\n    interview_data = {\\n        \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n        \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Python Developer\\\",\\n        \\\"interview_date\\\": \\\"2024-01-01\\\",\\n        \\\"questions\\\": {\\n            \\\"technical_questions\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is a decorator in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": [\\n                \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work with a difficult team member.\\\"\\n            ]\\n        },\\n        \\\"answers\\\": {\\n            \\\"technical_answers\\\": {\\n                \\\"What is a decorator in Python?\\\": \\\"A decorator is a function that takes another function as an argument and extends its behavior without modifying it.\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\": \\\"Lists are mutable, and tuples are immutable.\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"behavioral_answers\\\": {\\n                \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\": \\\"I once missed a deadline because I underestimated the complexity of the project.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work with a difficult team member.\\\": \\\"I had a team member who was always negative. I tried to understand their perspective and find common ground.\\\"\\n            }\\n        },\\n        \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": {},\\n        \\\"follow_up_answers\\\": {}\\n    }\\n\\n    # Evaluate the interview\\n    evaluations = evaluator.evaluate_interview(interview_data)\\n\\n    # Print the evaluations\\n    for question, evaluation in evaluations.items():\\n        print(f\\\"Question: {question}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  Relevance: {evaluation['relevance']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  Depth: {evaluation['depth']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  Confidence: {evaluation['confidence']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  Technical Accuracy: {evaluation['technical_accuracy']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"  Feedback: {evaluation['feedback']}\\\")\\n        print(\\\"-\\\" * 20)\\n```\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Develop Scoring Engine to aggregate match analysis and response evaluation into category scores across evaluation criteria.\\n  Result: ```python\\nclass ScoringEngine:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Aggregates match analysis and response evaluations into category scores\\n    across various evaluation criteria.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, match_analysis, interview_evaluations):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :param match_analysis: dict containing the match analysis report.\\n            Expected keys: 'skill_match', 'experience_match', 'education_match', 'overall_match'\\n            with numeric 'score' or boolean 'matched' fields.\\n        :param interview_evaluations: dict mapping question -> evaluation dict.\\n            Each evaluation must include:\\n                - type: 'technical' or 'behavioral'\\n                - relevance (0–5), depth (0–5), confidence (0–5)\\n                - technical_accuracy (0–5) for technical questions\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.match_analysis = match_analysis\\n        self.interview_evaluations = interview_evaluations\\n\\n    def calculate_match_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates the resume-job match score based on overall_match.\\n        :return: Match score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        overall = self.match_analysis.get(\\\"overall_match\\\", {}).get(\\\"score\\\", 0.0)\\n        return overall * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_technical_skill_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Combines skill_match (from match_analysis) and average technical_accuracy.\\n        :return: Technical skill score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        w_skill = 0.5\\n        w_interview = 0.5\\n\\n        # 0–1\\n        skill_match = self.match_analysis.get(\\\"skill_match\\\", {}).get(\\\"score\\\", 0.0)\\n\\n        # gather technical_accuracy from entries labeled as 'technical'\\n        tech_scores = []\\n        for eval in self.interview_evaluations.values():\\n            if eval.get(\\\"type\\\") == \\\"technical\\\":\\n                tech_scores.append(eval.get(\\\"technical_accuracy\\\", 0))\\n\\n        if tech_scores:\\n            avg_tech = sum(tech_scores) / len(tech_scores)  # 0–5\\n            avg_tech /= 5.0  # scale to 0–1\\n        else:\\n            avg_tech = 0.0\\n\\n        combined = w_skill * skill_match + w_interview * avg_tech\\n        return combined * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_problem_solving_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Uses depth and relevance of behavioral questions about problem-solving.\\n        :return: Problem-solving score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        scores = []\\n        for eval in self.interview_evaluations.values():\\n            if eval.get(\\\"type\\\") == \\\"behavioral\\\":\\n                # depth * relevance, max product = 25\\n                scores.append(eval.get(\\\"depth\\\", 0) * eval.get(\\\"relevance\\\", 0))\\n\\n        if not scores:\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n        avg = sum(scores) / len(scores)  # 0–25\\n        return (avg / 25.0) * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_communication_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Uses confidence and relevance across all questions.\\n        :return: Communication score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        scores = []\\n        for eval in self.interview_evaluations.values():\\n            # apply to all types\\n            scores.append(eval.get(\\\"confidence\\\", 0) * eval.get(\\\"relevance\\\", 0))\\n\\n        if not scores:\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n        avg = sum(scores) / len(scores)  # 0–25\\n        return (avg / 25.0) * 100\\n\\n    def calculate_overall_score(\\n        self,\\n        match_weight=0.2,\\n        technical_weight=0.4,\\n        problem_solving_weight=0.2,\\n        communication_weight=0.2\\n    ):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Weighted combination of match, technical, problem-solving, and communication.\\n        Weights must sum to 1.0.\\n        :return: Overall score (0–100)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # validate sum of weights\\n        total_w = match_weight + technical_weight + problem_solving_weight + communication_weight\\n        if abs(total_w - 1.0) > 1e-6:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\\"Weights must sum to 1.0, got {total_w}\\\")\\n\\n        m = self.calculate_match_score()\\n        t = self.calculate_technical_skill_score()\\n        p = self.calculate_problem_solving_score()\\n        c = self.calculate_communication_score()\\n\\n        overall = (\\n            match_weight * m +\\n            technical_weight * t +\\n            problem_solving_weight * p +\\n            communication_weight * c\\n        )\\n        return overall\\n\\n    def get_scoring_breakdown(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :return: dict with detailed scores for each category and overall.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        breakdown = {\\n            \\\"match\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_match_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Resume-job match score: {self.calculate_match_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"technical_skills\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_technical_skill_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Technical score: {self.calculate_technical_skill_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"problem_solving\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_problem_solving_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Problem-solving score: {self.calculate_problem_solving_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"communication\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_communication_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Communication score: {self.calculate_communication_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"overall\\\": {\\n                \\\"score\\\": self.calculate_overall_score(),\\n                \\\"details\\\": f\\\"Overall score: {self.calculate_overall_score():.2f}\\\"\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return breakdown\\n```\\nTask task8:\\n  Objective: Implement Follow-up Question Generation module to generate additional interview questions based on candidate responses and previous evaluation.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_questions, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up interview questions based on a candidate's response,\\n    history of asked questions, candidate profile, and job requirements.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's last response.\\n        previous_questions (list of str): Questions already asked.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate info, e.g. {'skills': [...], 'experience_years': X, ...}.\\n        job_description (str): Full text of the job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list of str: New follow-up questions (no duplicates of previous_questions).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Normalize\\n    prev = set(q.lower() for q in previous_questions)\\n    resp = candidate_response.strip()\\n    jd = job_description.lower()\\n\\n    # Extract concepts\\n    resp_skills = extract_skills(resp)\\n    resp_topics = extract_topics(resp)\\n    jd_skills = extract_skills(jd)\\n    gaps = identify_gaps(resp, candidate_profile, jd)\\n    inconsistencies = identify_inconsistencies(resp, candidate_profile)\\n\\n    follow_ups = []\\n\\n    # 1. Technical Deep Dive for each skill mentioned\\n    for skill in resp_skills:\\n        questions = [\\n            f\\\"Can you walk me through a specific project where you used {skill}? What were the main challenges and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            f\\\"What measurable impact did your work with {skill} have (e.g., performance improvements, cost savings)?\\\"\\n        ]\\n        for q in questions:\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 2. Align to Job-Required Skills not covered\\n    for skill in jd_skills:\\n        if skill not in resp_skills:\\n            q = f\\\"The JD emphasizes {skill}. Could you describe your experience with {skill}?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 3. Behavioral / STAR Probes for competency keywords\\n    competencies = [\\\"leadership\\\", \\\"teamwork\\\", \\\"problem-solving\\\", \\\"communication\\\", \\\"adaptability\\\"]\\n    for comp in competencies:\\n        if comp in jd:\\n            q = f\\\"Tell me about a time when you demonstrated {comp}. What was the Situation, Task, Action, and Result?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 4. Clarify vague or high-level statements\\n    vague_phrases = [\\\"various\\\", \\\"multiple\\\", \\\"significant\\\", \\\"extensive\\\"]\\n    for phrase in vague_phrases:\\n        if phrase in resp.lower():\\n            q = f\\\"You mentioned '{phrase}'. Could you give specific examples or metrics to illustrate that?\\\"\\n            if q.lower() not in prev:\\n                follow_ups.append(q)\\n            break  # only one such question\\n\\n    # 5. Address identified gaps\\n    for gap in gaps:\\n        q = f\\\"I noticed a gap: {gap}. Could you elaborate on this area?\\\"\\n        if q.lower() not in prev:\\n            follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    # 6. Query inconsistencies\\n    for inc in inconsistencies:\\n        q = f\\\"I saw a discrepancy: {inc}. Can you help me reconcile this?\\\"\\n        if q.lower() not in prev:\\n            follow_ups.append(q)\\n\\n    return follow_ups\\n\\n\\ndef extract_skills(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    A simple regex-based placeholder that finds capitalized words or common tech terms.\\n    Replace with NLP model or skills ontology in production.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    tech_terms = ['python', 'java', 'c++', 'aws', 'docker', 'kubernetes', 'sql', 'javascript']\\n    found = set()\\n    # match capitalized words (e.g., React, Django)\\n    for match in re.findall(r'\\\\b[A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9+\\\\-#]+\\\\b', text):\\n        found.add(match)\\n    # match known tech terms\\n    for term in tech_terms:\\n        if term in text.lower():\\n            found.add(term.title())\\n    return list(found)\\n\\n\\ndef extract_topics(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Placeholder: identify multi-word interest areas by common phrases.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    topics = []\\n    patterns = {\\n        'machine learning': r'machine learning',\\n        'cloud computing': r'cloud computing',\\n        'data engineering': r'data engineering',\\n        'project management': r'project management',\\n    }\\n    for name, pat in patterns.items():\\n        if re.search(pat, text, flags=re.I):\\n            topics.append(name.title())\\n    return topics\\n\\n\\ndef identify_gaps(candidate_response, candidate_profile, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Compare JD skills vs. response/profile. Highlight missing areas.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    gaps = []\\n    jd_skills = set(extract_skills(job_description.lower()))\\n    profile_skills = set(s.lower() for s in candidate_profile.get('skills', []))\\n    resp_skills = set(s.lower() for s in extract_skills(candidate_response))\\n    missing = jd_skills - (profile_skills | resp_skills)\\n    for skill in missing:\\n        gaps.append(f\\\"{skill} experience\\\")\\n    return gaps\\n\\n\\ndef identify_inconsistencies(candidate_response, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Flag contradictions, e.g. team size statements vs. profile.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    inc = []\\n    # example: candidate said 'led a team of X' but profile says different\\n    m = re.search(r'led a team of (\\\\d+)', candidate_response.lower())\\n    if m:\\n        claimed = int(m.group(1))\\n        actual = candidate_profile.get('team_size_led', 0)\\n        if claimed != actual:\\n            inc.append(f\\\"Claimed leading a team of {claimed} vs profile's {actual}\\\")\\n    return inc\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task7:\\n  Objective: Generate email templates for recruiter communications at two stages: interview invitation emails after match analysis and post-evaluation result emails after final report generation.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement Evaluation Report Generator to compile match analysis, interview summary, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendations into a .txt report.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass EvaluationReportGenerator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Compiles match analysis, interview data, assessments, strengths/weaknesses,\\n    and recommendations into a .txt report.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, candidate_name, job_title, match_analysis, interview_data, evaluations, scoring_breakdown, strengths, weaknesses, recommendation):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the EvaluationReportGenerator with candidate data, analysis, evaluations, scores, and recommendations.\\n\\n        :param candidate_name: str\\n        :param job_title: str\\n        :param match_analysis: dict (from MatchAnalyzer)\\n        :param interview_data: dict (questions and answers)\\n        :param evaluations: dict (from CandidateResponseEvaluator)\\n        :param scoring_breakdown: dict (from ScoringEngine)\\n        :param strengths: list of str\\n        :param weaknesses: list of str\\n        :param recommendation: str\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.candidate_name = candidate_name\\n        self.job_title = job_title\\n        self.match_analysis = match_analysis\\n        self.interview_data = interview_data\\n        self.evaluations = evaluations\\n        self.scoring_breakdown = scoring_breakdown\\n        self.strengths = strengths\\n        self.weaknesses = weaknesses\\n        self.recommendation = recommendation\\n\\n    def generate_report(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates the evaluation report in .txt format.\\n\\n        :return: str (the report content)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report = f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Candidate Evaluation Report\\n\\n        Candidate Name: {self.candidate_name}\\n        Job Title: {self.job_title}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        1. Resume-Job Match Analysis\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_match_analysis(self.match_analysis)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        2. Interview Summary\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_interview_summary(self.interview_data)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        3. Technical Assessment\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_technical_assessment(self.evaluations)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        4. Behavioral Assessment\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_behavioral_assessment(self.evaluations)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        5. Strengths\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_strengths(self.strengths)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        6. Weaknesses\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_weaknesses(self.weaknesses)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        7. Scoring Breakdown\\n        ================================================\\n        {self._format_scoring_breakdown(self.scoring_breakdown)}\\n\\n        ================================================\\n        8. Final Recommendation\\n        ================================================\\n        {self.recommendation}\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return report\\n\\n    def save_report(self, filename=\\\"candidate_evaluation_report.txt\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Saves the generated report to a .txt file.\\n\\n        :param filename: str (the name of the file to save the report to)\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report = self.generate_report()\\n        with open(filename, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n            f.write(report)\\n        print(f\\\"Report saved to {filename}\\\")\\n\\n    def _format_match_analysis(self, match_analysis):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the match analysis section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for key, value in match_analysis.items():\\n            report_string += f\\\"  {key.replace('_', ' ').title()}: {value.get('details', 'N/A')}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n    def _format_interview_summary(self, interview_data):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the interview summary section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for question_type in [\\\"technical_questions\\\", \\\"behavioral_questions\\\"]:\\n            report_string += f\\\"  {question_type.replace('_', ' ').title()}:\\\\n\\\"\\n            for question in interview_data[\\\"questions\\\"][question_type]:\\n                answer = interview_data[\\\"answers\\\"][question_type.replace(\\\"_questions\\\", \\\"_answers\\\")].get(question, \\\"No answer provided.\\\")\\n                report_string += f\\\"    - Question: {question}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"      Answer: {answer}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n    def _format_technical_assessment(self, evaluations):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the technical assessment section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for question, evaluation in evaluations.items():\\n            if \\\"technical\\\" in question.lower() or (\\\"technical\\\" in evaluation and evaluation[\\\"type\\\"] == \\\"technical\\\"):\\n                report_string += f\\\"  Question: {question}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Relevance: {evaluation['relevance']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Depth: {evaluation['depth']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Confidence: {evaluation['confidence']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Technical Accuracy: {evaluation['technical_accuracy']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Feedback: {evaluation['feedback']}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n    def _format_behavioral_assessment(self, evaluations):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the behavioral assessment section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for question, evaluation in evaluations.items():\\n             if \\\"behavioral\\\" in question.lower() or (\\\"behavioral\\\" in evaluation and evaluation[\\\"type\\\"] == \\\"behavioral\\\"):\\n                report_string += f\\\"  Question: {question}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Relevance: {evaluation['relevance']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Depth: {evaluation['depth']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Confidence: {evaluation['confidence']}\\\\n\\\"\\n                report_string += f\\\"    Feedback: {evaluation['feedback']}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n    def _format_strengths(self, strengths):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the strengths section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for strength in strengths:\\n            report_string += f\\\"  - {strength}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n    def _format_weaknesses(self, weaknesses):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the weaknesses section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for weakness in weaknesses:\\n            report_string += f\\\"  - {weakness}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n    def _format_scoring_breakdown(self, scoring_breakdown):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Formats the scoring breakdown section of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        report_string = \\\"\\\"\\n        for category, score_data in scoring_breakdown.items():\\n            report_string += f\\\"  {category.title()}: {score_data['details']}\\\\n\\\"\\n        return report_string\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage:\\n    match_analysis = {\\n        \\\"skill_match\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 0.8, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Skill match score: 0.80\\\"},\\n        \\\"experience_match\\\": {\\\"matched\\\": True, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Experience found matching job responsibilities.\\\"},\\n        \\\"education_match\\\": {\\\"matched\\\": True, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Education requirements met.\\\"},\\n        \\\"overall_match\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 0.75, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Overall match score: 0.75\\\"}\\n    }\\n\\n    interview_data = {\\n        \\\"questions\\\": {\\n            \\\"technical_questions\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is a decorator in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": [\\n                \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work with a difficult team member.\\\"\\n            ]\\n        },\\n        \\\"answers\\\": {\\n            \\\"technical_answers\\\": {\\n                \\\"What is a decorator in Python?\\\": \\\"A decorator is a function that takes another function as an argument and extends its behavior without modifying it.\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\": \\\"Lists are mutable, and tuples are immutable.\\\"\\n            },\\n            \\\"behavioral_answers\\\": {\\n                \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\": \\\"I once missed a deadline because I underestimated the complexity of the project.\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work with a difficult team member.\\\": \\\"I had a team member who was always negative. I tried to understand their perspective and find common ground.\\\"\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    evaluations = {\\n        \\\"What is a decorator in Python?\\\": {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": \\\"The candidate's answer was relevant and demonstrated good technical knowledge.\\\",\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"technical\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\": {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth\\\": 3,\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": \\\"The candidate's answer was relevant and demonstrated some technical knowledge.\\\",\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"technical\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\": {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": 3,\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": \\\"The candidate's answer was relevant to the behavioral question.\\\",\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"behavioral\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work with a difficult team member.\\\": {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"feedback\\\": \\\"The candidate's answer was relevant to the behavioral question.\\\",\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"behavioral\\\"\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    scoring_breakdown = {\\n        \\\"match\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 75.0, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Resume-job match score: 75.00\\\"},\\n        \\\"technical_skills\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 80.0, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Technical score: 80.00\\\"},\\n        \\\"problem_solving\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 70.0, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Problem-solving score: 70.00\\\"},\\n        \\\"communication\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 85.0, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Communication score: 85.00\\\"},\\n        \\\"overall\\\": {\\\"score\\\": 77.5, \\\"details\\\": \\\"Overall score: 77.50\\\"}\\n    }\\n\\n    strengths = [\\\"Strong Python skills\\\", \\\"Good communication skills\\\", \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\"]\\n    weaknesses = [\\\"Limited experience with React\\\", \\\"Could improve on providing more detailed answers\\\"]\\n    recommendation = \\\"Overall, the candidate is a good fit for the role. Recommend further consideration.\\\"\\n\\n    report_generator = EvaluationReportGenerator(\\\"John Doe\\\", \\\"Python Developer\\\", match_analysis, interview_data, evaluations, scoring_breakdown, strengths, weaknesses, recommendation)\\n    report_generator.save_report(\\\"john_doe_evaluation_report.txt\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:13:03.581209\"\n}"}
